1
00:00:01,635 --> 00:00:02,769
- Over here.
- My goodness.

2
00:00:02,769 --> 00:00:06,173
- We need to write down the menus.
- Okay.

3
00:00:06,173 --> 00:00:08,975
- Here.
- You should stay by my side

4
00:00:08,975 --> 00:00:10,877
- to check my handwriting.
- No, it's fine.

5
00:00:10,877 --> 00:00:12,946
I'm famous for my terrible handwriting.

6
00:00:12,946 --> 00:00:15,415
- Mine could be worse.
- No, I'm not kidding.

7
00:00:15,415 --> 00:00:17,150
Hey, where are you going? Hang on.

8
00:00:19,186 --> 00:00:21,021
I'm serious.

9
00:00:21,021 --> 00:00:22,823
I'm nervous.

10
00:00:22,823 --> 00:00:25,383
You don't need to be nervous at all.
We all have bad handwriting.

11
00:00:27,828 --> 00:00:29,029
My hand is shaking.

12
00:00:31,164 --> 00:00:33,233
That's totally fine. You pass.

13
00:00:33,233 --> 00:00:35,669
I can tell by how you wrote "Bon."

14
00:00:35,669 --> 00:00:37,204
There you go.

15
00:00:37,204 --> 00:00:38,605
It's perfect.

16
00:00:41,007 --> 00:00:43,477
- Hello.
- Hello.

17
00:00:43,477 --> 00:00:46,346
- We're open. Come by later.
- Hello.

18
00:00:46,346 --> 00:00:48,482
We're open, so come by.

19
00:00:48,482 --> 00:00:49,749
- Will you come?
- You're open?

20
00:00:49,749 --> 00:00:51,485
[Nods]
We'll be open later.

21
00:00:51,485 --> 00:00:53,353
- Come by.
- Okay.

22
00:00:54,955 --> 00:00:56,022
Yuzu Madeleine.

23
00:00:59,392 --> 00:01:00,627
- Bonjour...
- What was it?

24
00:01:00,627 --> 00:01:02,329
<i>Bokbunja</i> Madeleine.

25
00:01:02,329 --> 00:01:04,898
The blank spaces are bothering me.

26
00:01:04,898 --> 00:01:07,434
[Today's New Morning Menu]

27
00:01:07,434 --> 00:01:09,970
[Bonjour Strawberry Vanilla Mille-Feuille]

28
00:01:09,970 --> 00:01:12,739
[Bonjour Cherry Blossom Kouign-Amann]

29
00:01:12,739 --> 00:01:14,007
[Meanwhile In The Kitchen]

30
00:01:14,007 --> 00:01:16,207
[Café And Bakery
Commercial Kitchen Equipment Consulting]

31
00:01:16,877 --> 00:01:18,144
[Pacing]

32
00:01:18,144 --> 00:01:20,881
[From Side To Side]

33
00:01:28,989 --> 00:01:32,125
[Practicing Piping The Cream]

34
00:01:32,692 --> 00:01:35,996
[Which Signature Item
Is Making Him So Nervous Today?]

35
00:01:35,996 --> 00:01:38,398
[The French Say A Bakery Won't Last
If The Mille-Feuille Isn't Good]

36
00:01:38,398 --> 00:01:41,635
[A Staple French Dessert]

37
00:01:41,635 --> 00:01:45,739
[Mille-Feuille]

38
00:01:50,744 --> 00:01:53,580
[A Pastry With A Thousand Layers]

39
00:01:54,881 --> 00:01:58,218
[Paper-Thin Layers Of Pastry With Delicate Petals]

40
00:01:58,818 --> 00:02:04,090
[Topped With A Soft Vanilla Cream]

41
00:02:04,925 --> 00:02:09,329
[It's Made Even Sweeter With Gochang Strawberries!]

42
00:02:09,329 --> 00:02:10,697
[Bonjour Bakery]

43
00:02:12,165 --> 00:02:15,168
[Bonjour Strawberry Vanilla Mille-Feuille]

44
00:02:15,168 --> 00:02:20,473
[Make The Strawberry Vanilla Mille-Feuille]

45
00:02:25,946 --> 00:02:29,683
[Pricking The Dough To Prevent Over-Rising]

46
00:02:34,521 --> 00:02:36,756
[You Need To Trim It Precisely]

47
00:02:41,461 --> 00:02:43,663
[Cut Into 4.5cm Wide Strips]

48
00:03:03,683 --> 00:03:06,219
[Put The Trimmed Dough In The Oven]

49
00:03:06,219 --> 00:03:10,056
[And Bake For 25 Minutes]

50
00:03:14,027 --> 00:03:18,565
[The Dough Is Slowly Rising]

51
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:24,571
[It's Only Been 10 Minutes.
Why Is He Opening The Oven Already?]

52
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:32,412
[It Looks Pale And Underbaked...]

53
00:03:34,014 --> 00:03:35,815
[Parchment Paper]

54
00:03:38,585 --> 00:03:41,688
[Why Did He Place A Metal Tray On Top?]

55
00:03:43,957 --> 00:03:48,728
[The Tray Ensures Flat, Even Layers]

56
00:03:49,529 --> 00:03:54,434
[Bake With The Tray On Top
For Another 15 Minutes]

57
00:03:54,434 --> 00:03:58,571
[15 Minutes Later]

58
00:04:12,218 --> 00:04:15,121
[A Flat Pastry With Countless Layers]

59
00:04:15,655 --> 00:04:20,493
[2nd Round Of Trimming]

60
00:04:28,868 --> 00:04:33,173
[Cut The Pastry Into 3.5cm Pieces]

61
00:04:38,511 --> 00:04:41,247
[Lightly Dust Them With Powdered Sugar]

62
00:04:42,415 --> 00:04:44,484
[Why Dust It With Powdered Sugar?]

63
00:04:44,484 --> 00:04:47,620
[As The Powdered Sugar Melts,
It Keeps The Mille-Feuille Crisp]

64
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:50,256
[3 Minutes Later]

65
00:04:55,729 --> 00:04:59,733
[It's Just Like Sugar-Coated Puff Pastry]

66
00:05:07,574 --> 00:05:10,210
There are 2, 4, 6, 8, 10...

67
00:05:10,210 --> 00:05:14,748
[The Pastry Is Ready,
It's Time To Pipe The Cream]

68
00:05:18,952 --> 00:05:20,620
[Strawberry Cream]

69
00:05:34,834 --> 00:05:36,336
[No Cream]

70
00:05:44,577 --> 00:05:46,846
[Strawberry Coulis (Syrup)]

71
00:05:46,846 --> 00:05:50,784
[Squeeze The Strawberry Syrup
Into The Strawberry Cream]

72
00:05:57,123 --> 00:05:58,691
[A Small Dollop]

73
00:06:02,162 --> 00:06:05,565
[Once The Plump Dollops Of Cream Are Piped,
It's Left To Set Briefly In The Fridge]

74
00:06:06,666 --> 00:06:10,303
[Now It's Time To Stack The Mille-Feuille]

75
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:19,646
[Why Is It Facing Up?]

76
00:06:19,646 --> 00:06:23,049
[A Traditional Mille-Feuille
Is Laid Horizontally]

77
00:06:24,350 --> 00:06:27,187
[But Bonjour Mille-Feuille Is Different]

78
00:06:27,854 --> 00:06:33,092
[A Plain Pastry Piece Is Paired]

79
00:06:33,626 --> 00:06:37,430
[With A Piped Pastry Piece]

80
00:06:39,165 --> 00:06:43,770
[And Add 3 More Pastry Pieces With Cream]

81
00:06:48,474 --> 00:06:51,578
[Made Easier For Seniors To Enjoy]

82
00:06:52,045 --> 00:06:55,548
[Introducing A New Vertical Mille-Feuille]

83
00:07:05,258 --> 00:07:09,128
[The King Of Baking Uses His Full Focus]

84
00:07:09,762 --> 00:07:12,565
[To Create The Bold But Graceful]

85
00:07:12,565 --> 00:07:17,070
[Waves Of Cream]

86
00:07:27,413 --> 00:07:32,085
[Shaking]

87
00:07:43,496 --> 00:07:46,466
[The Secret To Perfect Wavy Cream]

88
00:07:46,466 --> 00:07:50,536
[It's Running Practice Simulations]

89
00:07:56,542 --> 00:07:59,913
[Wavy Cream]

90
00:07:59,913 --> 00:08:02,849
[Piped With Intense Focus]

91
00:08:02,849 --> 00:08:04,751
- What do you think?
- You did so well.

92
00:08:05,251 --> 00:08:06,185
Take a look, already.

93
00:08:06,185 --> 00:08:07,453
[Staff Cheering]

94
00:08:08,454 --> 00:08:10,089
[Excellent Work!]

95
00:08:10,089 --> 00:08:12,058
Look at it.

96
00:08:13,026 --> 00:08:15,162
Take a closer look.

97
00:08:15,162 --> 00:08:17,096
[He's Hungry For Compliments]

98
00:08:17,096 --> 00:08:19,165
Jeez.

99
00:08:22,101 --> 00:08:24,137
[Top It With Gochang Strawberries]

100
00:08:26,706 --> 00:08:29,542
[And Drops Of Strawberry Syrup]

101
00:08:36,382 --> 00:08:38,051
- What do you think?
- It's so pretty.

102
00:08:38,051 --> 00:08:39,686
- Does it look okay?
- Yes.

103
00:08:46,392 --> 00:08:48,428
[Nervous Gulp]

104
00:08:49,629 --> 00:08:51,130
I see a senior lady.

105
00:08:51,831 --> 00:08:54,834
[Hurrying Over]

106
00:08:55,668 --> 00:08:57,704
[The First Customer Has Arrived]

107
00:08:57,704 --> 00:09:00,139
- Welcome!
- Hello.

108
00:09:01,474 --> 00:09:02,942
- Welcome!
- Welcome!

109
00:09:02,942 --> 00:09:04,277
Hello, ma'am.

110
00:09:04,277 --> 00:09:07,413
You're the best, Joo Bin.

111
00:09:07,413 --> 00:09:09,716
- Hello.
- Welcome.

112
00:09:09,716 --> 00:09:13,052
- Did you happen to be passing by?
- What?

113
00:09:13,052 --> 00:09:14,220
I live here.

114
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,955
- Oh, you live nearby.
- Yes.

115
00:09:15,955 --> 00:09:18,958
[Sitting Separately]
They stopped by to buy some bread.

116
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:21,060
- Why are you sitting apart?
- Why are you sitting apart?

117
00:09:21,060 --> 00:09:22,295
You should sit together.

118
00:09:22,295 --> 00:09:24,697
Come and sit here.

119
00:09:24,697 --> 00:09:27,700
- Did you guys have a fight?
- What?

120
00:09:27,700 --> 00:09:29,969
Did you two argue?

121
00:09:29,969 --> 00:09:31,337
Why are you sitting apart?

122
00:09:31,337 --> 00:09:32,638
[They Didn't Have A Fight]

123
00:09:32,638 --> 00:09:34,540
Honestly, our menu is...

124
00:09:34,540 --> 00:09:36,109
Do you like coffee?

125
00:09:36,109 --> 00:09:38,277
I'm more interested in the bread.

126
00:09:38,277 --> 00:09:40,113
- You want some bread?
- I want to take some to go

127
00:09:40,113 --> 00:09:41,681
so I can eat them at home.

128
00:09:41,681 --> 00:09:42,915
You want to take them home?

129
00:09:42,915 --> 00:09:46,686
- You don't want to eat here?
- Should we eat something here?

130
00:09:46,686 --> 00:09:48,788
Who has the time for that?

131
00:09:48,788 --> 00:09:50,523
Who has the time for that?

132
00:09:50,523 --> 00:09:52,725
[You're Leaving Already?]

133
00:09:52,725 --> 00:09:54,794
So you'll eat at home?

134
00:09:54,794 --> 00:09:56,029
What are you thinking?

135
00:09:56,029 --> 00:09:57,063
[Feeling Pressured]

136
00:09:57,063 --> 00:10:00,466
- We'll just have a small bite here.
- Would you like to do that?

137
00:10:00,466 --> 00:10:03,503
- Yes.
- In that case, do you like sweet things?

138
00:10:03,503 --> 00:10:05,171
- Sweet things?
- You don't like sweet things?

139
00:10:05,171 --> 00:10:07,673
- He doesn't-
- I don't know what tastes good.

140
00:10:07,673 --> 00:10:09,242
I'm too old.

141
00:10:09,242 --> 00:10:12,211
- They're all newfangled foods.
- That's true.

142
00:10:12,211 --> 00:10:15,915
I've lived a long life. I'm 91 years old.

143
00:10:16,482 --> 00:10:17,383
But...

144
00:10:17,383 --> 00:10:18,851
So what can I possibly know?

145
00:10:18,851 --> 00:10:21,320
But you look so young for your age.

146
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:23,589
I'm honestly so surprised right now.

147
00:10:23,589 --> 00:10:25,825
- Is your surname Kim?
- It's Kim.

148
00:10:25,825 --> 00:10:27,160
I'm Kim Seon Ho.

149
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:29,262
What's your family clan?

150
00:10:29,262 --> 00:10:31,497
[A Korean Senior's Way Of Showing Affection]
The thing about my surname is...

151
00:10:31,497 --> 00:10:33,599
I come from an unusual branch.

152
00:10:33,599 --> 00:10:35,902
Have you heard of the Haeum Kim clan?

153
00:10:35,902 --> 00:10:37,670
- Haeum.
- Hawon?

154
00:10:37,670 --> 00:10:39,405
- Haeum.
- Haeum.

155
00:10:39,405 --> 00:10:41,507
[A Rare Clan With Only 400 Members]
Yes, I'm from the Haeum Kim clan.

156
00:10:41,507 --> 00:10:44,444
[I'll Have What You Recommend]
I've tried this, and it's really good.

157
00:10:44,444 --> 00:10:46,512
- Do you want to try this one?
- Yes, we'll eat that here.

158
00:10:46,512 --> 00:10:47,914
Yes, try this one here.

159
00:10:47,914 --> 00:10:49,182
We'll serve tea on the house.

160
00:10:49,182 --> 00:10:51,517
Are you okay with a hot tea?

161
00:10:51,517 --> 00:10:53,186
- Just give us anything.
- Anything?

162
00:10:53,186 --> 00:10:54,607
Okay.

163
00:10:55,588 --> 00:10:56,589
We'll serve tea on the house.

164
00:10:56,589 --> 00:10:58,858
[Talking About Hot Tea On The House]
Are you okay with a hot tea?

165
00:10:58,858 --> 00:11:00,560
- Just give us anything.
- Anything?

166
00:11:00,560 --> 00:11:02,562
[I'm On It!]
Okay.

167
00:11:02,562 --> 00:11:04,097
[Preparing The Tea]
All right.

168
00:11:04,097 --> 00:11:05,198
Chamomile tea...

169
00:11:05,198 --> 00:11:07,133
- Oh, you already know.
- Yes.

170
00:11:07,133 --> 00:11:09,487
- Do you have part-time experience?
- Yes.

171
00:11:11,237 --> 00:11:12,305
[While The Experienced Team]
All right.

172
00:11:12,305 --> 00:11:13,840
[Get The Order Ready]
If you make it...

173
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:15,065
Yes?

174
00:11:16,175 --> 00:11:18,311
You had to be young to try this stuff.

175
00:11:18,311 --> 00:11:20,028
We're too old.

176
00:11:21,314 --> 00:11:26,252
[As They May Feel A Little Awkward
In This New Environment]

177
00:11:28,321 --> 00:11:31,090
- Oh, sorry.
- I'm going over.

178
00:11:31,090 --> 00:11:32,592
Are you on your way back from somewhere?

179
00:11:32,592 --> 00:11:34,160
[Manager Hee Ae Steps In]
Yes.

180
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:36,095
We went to see the dentist.

181
00:11:36,095 --> 00:11:37,697
We've made various stops.

182
00:11:37,697 --> 00:11:41,334
You even went to the dentist
this early in the morning?

183
00:11:41,334 --> 00:11:43,603
My teeth aren't in great shape,

184
00:11:43,603 --> 00:11:45,938
so I have full dentures.

185
00:11:45,938 --> 00:11:48,040
- Do you have full dentures?
- Yes.

186
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:49,509
I see.

187
00:11:49,509 --> 00:11:52,059
But they look so natural.

188
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:54,881
Steep it a bit,

189
00:11:54,881 --> 00:11:56,616
- then move the teabag here.
- Okay.

190
00:11:56,616 --> 00:11:58,217
- Just put it in there.
- Okay.

191
00:11:58,217 --> 00:12:00,820
I'll be back in a flash
with the Strawberry Mille-Feuille.

192
00:12:00,820 --> 00:12:01,821
[Just Then]

193
00:12:03,156 --> 00:12:04,757
[Another Customer Has Arrived]

194
00:12:04,757 --> 00:12:06,926
Is someone coming? Someone's here.

195
00:12:06,926 --> 00:12:08,794
- Hello.
- Hello.

196
00:12:09,295 --> 00:12:11,255
[Lives In The House Behind The Bakery
Park Heon Gu]

197
00:12:11,631 --> 00:12:13,032
[They Know Each Other]

198
00:12:13,032 --> 00:12:15,168
- Welcome. Have a seat here.
- Sit here.

199
00:12:15,168 --> 00:12:17,170
- Give me 10,000 on worth.
- You want 10,000 won worth?

200
00:12:17,170 --> 00:12:19,605
Okay, take a seat while you wait.

201
00:12:19,605 --> 00:12:21,223
Make yourself at home.

202
00:12:22,241 --> 00:12:24,177
Gosh, I'm tired.

203
00:12:25,178 --> 00:12:26,179
[On Day 2 Of Business]

204
00:12:26,179 --> 00:12:27,914
My daughter said you had rice cake sticks.

205
00:12:27,914 --> 00:12:29,682
- Cash?
- Rice cake sticks.

206
00:12:29,682 --> 00:12:31,083
- Oh, rice cake sticks?
- Yes.

207
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:32,251
Don't you know what that is?

208
00:12:32,251 --> 00:12:33,519
- Rice cake sticks?
- Yes.

209
00:12:33,519 --> 00:12:35,143
We don't sell those.

210
00:12:36,322 --> 00:12:37,890
[In The Same Seat]
Would you like a hot coffee?

211
00:12:37,890 --> 00:12:39,425
- What?
- Coffee.

212
00:12:39,425 --> 00:12:41,460
[What Would You Like Today?]
Coffee or tea?

213
00:12:41,460 --> 00:12:45,031
- Green tea or chamomile tea?
- Do you...

214
00:12:45,031 --> 00:12:47,166
- Do you have ginger tea?
- Ginger tea?

215
00:12:47,166 --> 00:12:49,468
We don't have any ginger tea,

216
00:12:49,468 --> 00:12:51,571
but we do have regular tea.

217
00:12:51,571 --> 00:12:53,339
Will you have it here?

218
00:12:53,339 --> 00:12:54,407
I need to take it with me.

219
00:12:54,407 --> 00:12:57,276
Oh, you want to take it with you?

220
00:12:57,276 --> 00:12:58,844
[He Wants To Pay Upfront Again]

221
00:12:58,844 --> 00:13:00,146
I'll take this when you leave...

222
00:13:00,146 --> 00:13:02,582
Okay, I'll just take it now.

223
00:13:02,582 --> 00:13:06,452
[Putting Together A Custom Package]
How about two of these and a kouign-amann?

224
00:13:06,452 --> 00:13:09,255
- Throw in a kouign-amann for sure.
- One of those and...

225
00:13:09,255 --> 00:13:11,524
[Tried And Tested]
Let's throw in a croissant as well.

226
00:13:11,524 --> 00:13:15,761
- A croissant? Okay, good choice.
- And maybe a financier...

227
00:13:15,761 --> 00:13:17,296
[While The Goods Are Being Wrapped Up]

228
00:13:17,296 --> 00:13:18,598
And one of these...

229
00:13:18,598 --> 00:13:21,601
Sir, would you like a hot drink?

230
00:13:21,601 --> 00:13:23,803
- Yeah.
- Let me get you a hot drink.

231
00:13:23,803 --> 00:13:27,106
[Honey Lemon Tea,
As Sweet And Refreshing As Ginger Tea]

232
00:13:27,106 --> 00:13:28,708
Here you go, sir.

233
00:13:28,708 --> 00:13:30,176
It's on the house.

234
00:13:30,176 --> 00:13:32,078
- You don't need to pay for this.
- Okay.

235
00:13:32,078 --> 00:13:34,146
It's made with lemon.

236
00:13:34,146 --> 00:13:36,816
It doesn't contain ginger,
but it tastes similar.

237
00:13:36,816 --> 00:13:38,818
Give it a try.

238
00:13:42,288 --> 00:13:45,458
[Once Again, Mr. Park Heon Gu]

239
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:51,230
[Bought Baked Goods For His Wife,
Who Has Trouble Walking]

240
00:13:53,432 --> 00:13:57,837
[And They Enjoyed
Bonjour Bakery's New Item Together]

241
00:13:59,839 --> 00:14:00,822
- Seon Ho.
- Yes?

242
00:14:00,822 --> 00:14:02,074
This dessert is very fragile.

243
00:14:02,074 --> 00:14:03,743
- So...
- Did you knock it over by shaking it?

244
00:14:03,743 --> 00:14:05,151
- No, I didn't.
- No?

245
00:14:05,151 --> 00:14:06,412
- Anyways,
- Are you sure?

246
00:14:06,412 --> 00:14:09,181
- you must be careful.
- Okay.

247
00:14:09,181 --> 00:14:12,451
Take it over to the customers, Ki Taek.

248
00:14:13,152 --> 00:14:15,087
- Hello.
- Hello.

249
00:14:15,488 --> 00:14:17,323
We made this mille-feuille nabe ourselves.

250
00:14:17,323 --> 00:14:19,759
I mean, mille-feuille is freshly baked.

251
00:14:19,759 --> 00:14:21,560
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

252
00:14:21,560 --> 00:14:24,697
We'll enjoy it.

253
00:14:25,731 --> 00:14:27,500
This...

254
00:14:29,902 --> 00:14:34,073
[She Gives The First Slice To Her Husband]

255
00:14:34,907 --> 00:14:37,027
[Then Scrapes The Strawberry Cream
Off The Paper Liner]

256
00:14:40,413 --> 00:14:42,114
[Glances Over]

257
00:14:44,984 --> 00:14:48,988
[She Cuts Her Husband's Slice
Into Smaller Pieces]

258
00:14:52,525 --> 00:14:54,927
[At Last, Her Husband,
Who's Had Trouble With His Teeth,]

259
00:14:54,927 --> 00:14:58,364
[Can Comfortably Enjoy The Mille-Feuille]

260
00:15:02,301 --> 00:15:03,670
Ma'am.

261
00:15:04,303 --> 00:15:05,571
Do you like it?

262
00:15:05,571 --> 00:15:07,603
Yes, it's tasty.

263
00:15:08,841 --> 00:15:11,243
This is the benefit of a long life.

264
00:15:11,243 --> 00:15:12,545
Why?

265
00:15:12,545 --> 00:15:15,214
- You're right.
- I'm 91 years old,

266
00:15:15,214 --> 00:15:17,083
and I've never tried this before.

267
00:15:17,083 --> 00:15:18,150
I see.

268
00:15:18,150 --> 00:15:19,819
And it's so tasty.

269
00:15:19,819 --> 00:15:21,554
You've never had it before?

270
00:15:21,554 --> 00:15:23,622
Of course, I haven't.

271
00:15:23,622 --> 00:15:25,024
Even if we have the money,

272
00:15:25,024 --> 00:15:28,060
we don't know where to go
to get food like this,

273
00:15:28,060 --> 00:15:30,012
so we can't experience it.

274
00:15:31,864 --> 00:15:34,200
I don't know my way around Gochang,

275
00:15:34,200 --> 00:15:36,967
so I always take my wife with me.

276
00:15:38,337 --> 00:15:41,307
She's 86 years old now,

277
00:15:41,307 --> 00:15:44,977
but she's sharper than I am,

278
00:15:44,977 --> 00:15:46,684
so she's my right-hand woman.

279
00:15:50,015 --> 00:15:51,951
You look healthy as well.

280
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:53,285
You seem to be in good shape.

281
00:15:53,285 --> 00:15:54,453
What is this?

282
00:15:54,453 --> 00:15:56,188
[Awkwardly Changes The Topic]

283
00:15:57,056 --> 00:16:00,794
You know what makes
children appreciate their parents?

284
00:16:00,794 --> 00:16:03,863
They appreciate you most after you die,

285
00:16:03,863 --> 00:16:05,681
as they mourn over your death.

286
00:16:06,465 --> 00:16:08,067
That's when they appreciate you.

287
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:09,347
[His Right-Hand Woman Is Rattled]

288
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:12,838
- Right?
- Stop talking and just eat.

289
00:16:12,838 --> 00:16:16,342
If you end up like me
and live until you're 91 years old,

290
00:16:16,342 --> 00:16:18,477
your children get sick of you.

291
00:16:18,477 --> 00:16:19,578
[Mr. Kim Protests]
That's not true.

292
00:16:19,578 --> 00:16:22,081
I want my parents
to live a long and healthy life.

293
00:16:22,615 --> 00:16:23,916
It's a living hell.

294
00:16:23,916 --> 00:16:25,885
- Really?
- That's right.

295
00:16:25,885 --> 00:16:28,320
I still live with my parents and-

296
00:16:28,320 --> 00:16:29,789
But...

297
00:16:29,789 --> 00:16:32,358
What are you saying? Just eat.

298
00:16:32,358 --> 00:16:34,226
[He Does As He's Told]

299
00:16:34,226 --> 00:16:38,405
It's so nice to see you
still spending time together like this.

300
00:16:40,566 --> 00:16:43,135
- That was good.
- Good.

301
00:16:43,135 --> 00:16:45,571
- I feel like I've been recharged.
- Right?

302
00:16:45,571 --> 00:16:47,706
It gives you energy.

303
00:16:47,706 --> 00:16:49,275
That's right.

304
00:16:49,275 --> 00:16:51,444
- We enjoyed it.
- Thank you.

305
00:16:51,444 --> 00:16:54,125
- Since I don't have good teeth,
- Yes?

306
00:16:54,125 --> 00:16:57,650
Soft and chewy food is the best.

307
00:16:57,650 --> 00:16:59,118
[I'll Get Going First]
Hard food is...

308
00:16:59,118 --> 00:17:01,387
Take care.

309
00:17:03,088 --> 00:17:06,325
[They Really Didn't Have A Fight]

310
00:17:06,325 --> 00:17:07,626
She's leaving by herself.

311
00:17:07,626 --> 00:17:09,962
[They're Used To Doing Their Own Thing]
Thanks for all your hard work helping us.

312
00:17:09,962 --> 00:17:11,590
Don't mention it.

313
00:17:14,934 --> 00:17:16,303
All good?

314
00:17:17,536 --> 00:17:18,477
Thank you.

315
00:17:18,477 --> 00:17:20,506
- Thanks for your service.
- Thank you.

316
00:17:20,506 --> 00:17:23,079
- Goodbye.
- Take care.

317
00:17:29,415 --> 00:17:34,553
<i>I got married when I was 26 years old.</i>

318
00:17:35,321 --> 00:17:36,822
<i>After we got married,</i>

319
00:17:36,822 --> 00:17:40,259
<i>I bought a house with just one room
and nothing but electricity,</i>

320
00:17:40,259 --> 00:17:43,395
<i>and fixed it up with my own hands.</i>

321
00:17:43,395 --> 00:17:45,564
<i>I even built the annex myself.</i>

322
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:50,669
I need to cut it up for my husband.

323
00:17:50,669 --> 00:17:53,005
[They Enjoy The Finely Cut Croissant]

324
00:17:53,005 --> 00:17:54,306
Let's have a glass of rice wine.

325
00:17:54,306 --> 00:17:58,611
[With A Glass Of <i>Makgeolli</i>]

326
00:17:59,078 --> 00:18:01,680
You'll notice she hardly ever rests.

327
00:18:02,147 --> 00:18:06,069
It's a truly refreshing experience.

328
00:18:08,654 --> 00:18:11,690
She's been through a lot living with me.

329
00:18:12,892 --> 00:18:14,827
I don't have much money.

330
00:18:14,827 --> 00:18:17,130
Imagine how hard it's been on her.

331
00:18:17,130 --> 00:18:20,899
<i>I couldn't leave him behind,
so I stayed with him.</i>

332
00:18:21,901 --> 00:18:25,271
I have no way to repay her.

333
00:18:25,271 --> 00:18:27,606
I just feel extremely grateful.

334
00:18:27,606 --> 00:18:31,176
My heart is full of gratitude.

335
00:18:31,176 --> 00:18:32,945
Just know that.

336
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:35,314
We need to be good to each other

337
00:18:35,314 --> 00:18:37,917
since we don't have long left to live.

338
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:42,121
[Anything You'd Like To Say To Your Wife?]

339
00:18:45,731 --> 00:18:47,626
Honey, you've been through a lot,

340
00:18:47,626 --> 00:18:49,161
marrying a man like me

341
00:18:49,161 --> 00:18:51,949
who had nothing to offer.

342
00:18:56,502 --> 00:18:58,989
- Sir...
- Has she been through a lot?

343
00:19:09,348 --> 00:19:11,985
<i>I love you, Cho Sun Ja!</i>

344
00:19:14,353 --> 00:19:18,357
[Bonjour Bakery]

345
00:19:20,626 --> 00:19:24,096
I think that dessert lifted his spirits.

346
00:19:24,096 --> 00:19:25,864
I felt a bit bad

347
00:19:25,864 --> 00:19:28,668
because they just wanted
to buy something to go.

348
00:19:28,668 --> 00:19:29,835
But I made them stay.

349
00:19:29,835 --> 00:19:31,870
I was like, "You have to stay for a bite."

350
00:19:31,870 --> 00:19:35,240
- He said he felt recharged.
- Did he say that? That's a relief.

351
00:19:35,240 --> 00:19:37,016
You did well.

352
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:43,349
Look at her.

353
00:19:43,349 --> 00:19:47,286
She's very efficient,
but she came on a slow day.

354
00:19:47,286 --> 00:19:49,455
I feel too awkward to just stand around.

355
00:19:49,455 --> 00:19:52,484
Did all our customers come by last week?

356
00:19:54,660 --> 00:19:56,462
Am I not spreading the word enough?

357
00:19:56,462 --> 00:19:57,963
Why aren't we going viral?

358
00:19:57,963 --> 00:20:00,232
We don't seem to be a hit.

359
00:20:00,766 --> 00:20:02,935
[Waiting For The Customers
Who Are A No-Show]

360
00:20:02,935 --> 00:20:05,337
[Bonjour Bakery's Guardian Dog]

361
00:20:10,909 --> 00:20:13,479
Now I get how café managers feel.

362
00:20:13,479 --> 00:20:15,981
I used to wonder why they sat outside.

363
00:20:27,126 --> 00:20:28,927
- Hello.
- Hi.

364
00:20:28,927 --> 00:20:29,828
Hello, where are you going?

365
00:20:29,828 --> 00:20:31,196
[Just Happy To See A Face]
The local clinic.

366
00:20:31,196 --> 00:20:32,498
- Local clinic?
- Yes.

367
00:20:32,498 --> 00:20:34,066
- We just opened a café.
- Okay.

368
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:34,967
[Kim Il Nam]
Come visit us-

369
00:20:34,967 --> 00:20:36,135
I got hurt while exercising.

370
00:20:36,135 --> 00:20:38,470
- Come visit us next time.
- All right.

371
00:20:38,470 --> 00:20:40,406
- I'll be waiting.
- Okay.

372
00:20:40,406 --> 00:20:41,807
[Giggling]
The local clinic...

373
00:20:41,807 --> 00:20:43,075
Hello.

374
00:20:43,075 --> 00:20:44,410
- Where are you headed?
- Me?

375
00:20:44,410 --> 00:20:46,311
- Yes.
- I'm going to get something from my car.

376
00:20:46,311 --> 00:20:47,212
- Your car?
- Yeah.

377
00:20:47,212 --> 00:20:48,514
Why not drop by our café?

378
00:20:48,514 --> 00:20:50,416
I came by yesterday,
but you weren't around.

379
00:20:50,416 --> 00:20:53,452
I had a performance yesterday,
so I couldn't be here.

380
00:20:53,452 --> 00:20:55,487
[Seon Ho's Longtime Fan]
But I'm on shift today.

381
00:20:55,487 --> 00:20:57,423
- I'll come by for a tea later.
- A cup of tea?

382
00:20:57,423 --> 00:20:59,425
I can make a good cup of tea.

383
00:20:59,425 --> 00:21:01,126
Come by any time.

384
00:21:01,126 --> 00:21:02,695
[A Chance Encounter
With Her Favorite Celebrity]

385
00:21:02,695 --> 00:21:04,296
What are you getting from your car?

386
00:21:04,296 --> 00:21:05,764
I left my...

387
00:21:05,764 --> 00:21:08,847
I left my... What was it?

388
00:21:12,071 --> 00:21:13,572
[Ticklish]
What was it?

389
00:21:13,572 --> 00:21:15,174
- What was I going to get?
- What was it?

390
00:21:15,174 --> 00:21:17,342
- Are you just going?
- No, I need to get something.

391
00:21:17,342 --> 00:21:19,044
- Is it something heavy?
- No.

392
00:21:19,044 --> 00:21:20,045
- Do you need help?
- No.

393
00:21:20,045 --> 00:21:21,281
Is it okay?

394
00:21:21,281 --> 00:21:23,982
- Okay, I'll see you later.
- Okay.

395
00:21:23,982 --> 00:21:25,451
- See you later.
- Bye.

396
00:21:25,451 --> 00:21:26,351
Hello.

397
00:21:26,351 --> 00:21:28,053
[Salesman On A Mission]

398
00:21:28,053 --> 00:21:29,688
Our café... Oh, hello again.

399
00:21:29,688 --> 00:21:31,290
We met earlier.

400
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:33,325
We're open.

401
00:21:33,325 --> 00:21:35,928
We came and had some desserts yesterday.

402
00:21:35,928 --> 00:21:37,730
But I wasn't here yesterday.

403
00:21:37,730 --> 00:21:39,198
The coffee tastes different today

404
00:21:39,198 --> 00:21:40,599
- since I'm making it.
- Sure.

405
00:21:40,599 --> 00:21:42,534
We even spread the word
about how good all the food is

406
00:21:42,534 --> 00:21:44,937
- to get more people to come.
- Did you?

407
00:21:44,937 --> 00:21:46,338
Hasn't the word spread enough yet?

408
00:21:46,338 --> 00:21:47,740
We went on about it.

409
00:21:47,740 --> 00:21:49,675
I've been telling everyone
in this neighborhood.

410
00:21:49,675 --> 00:21:51,477
It's been frustratingly quiet.

411
00:21:51,477 --> 00:21:52,860
Has it?

412
00:21:53,746 --> 00:21:55,147
It's a wonder.

413
00:21:55,147 --> 00:21:56,882
- Why isn't anyone coming?
- It's the countryside.

414
00:21:56,882 --> 00:21:59,685
- They won't spend much.
- Is that why?

415
00:21:59,685 --> 00:22:01,887
- Come by if you get bored.
- Okay.

416
00:22:01,887 --> 00:22:03,537
I'll make you a coffee.

417
00:22:07,031 --> 00:22:08,433
[As For The Customer Who Left]

418
00:22:09,862 --> 00:22:14,266
[It Seems She Felt Bad
For The Downcast Young Barista]

419
00:22:16,135 --> 00:22:18,871
[She Returns To The Bakery With Her Friend]

420
00:22:18,871 --> 00:22:21,006
- Someone's here.
- Welcome.

421
00:22:21,006 --> 00:22:22,407
Hello, come on in.

422
00:22:22,407 --> 00:22:23,335
[Kim Yeong Suk, Im Yang Taek]

423
00:22:23,335 --> 00:22:25,611
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

424
00:22:25,611 --> 00:22:27,946
- Welcome.
- We planned to come with the health center director.

425
00:22:27,946 --> 00:22:30,315
- They're coming as a group.
- Where... The director?

426
00:22:30,315 --> 00:22:32,050
- We'll be back.
- We'll come back with her.

427
00:22:32,050 --> 00:22:34,987
But wait, when will you be back?

428
00:22:34,987 --> 00:22:37,856
- We made a reservation for 1 p.m.
- You have a reservation?

429
00:22:37,856 --> 00:22:39,792
- We arranged it ourselves.
- Oh, I see.

430
00:22:39,792 --> 00:22:40,893
- We do take reservations.
- Okay.

431
00:22:40,893 --> 00:22:44,062
- See you at 1 p.m.
- We arranged to meet at 1 p.m.

432
00:22:44,062 --> 00:22:45,364
- See you at 1 p.m.
- Okay.

433
00:22:45,364 --> 00:22:47,868
[And Just Like That, Reservations Are Open]
Okay.

434
00:22:48,967 --> 00:22:50,302
See you at 1 p.m.

435
00:22:50,302 --> 00:22:51,837
- All right.
- All right.

436
00:22:53,539 --> 00:22:55,289
They made a reservation.

437
00:22:57,009 --> 00:22:59,344
- I didn't know we took reservations.
- They have to come now.

438
00:22:59,344 --> 00:23:01,613
[Reservations Are Now Available]
They said they'd come at 1 p.m.

439
00:23:01,613 --> 00:23:02,681
We take reservations now.

440
00:23:02,681 --> 00:23:04,583
I wonder if we're on CatchTable.

441
00:23:04,583 --> 00:23:07,271
[1 p.m. Reservation - Kim Yeong Suk
And Im Yang Taek With Health Center Director]

442
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:10,088
[12:50 p.m.]

443
00:23:12,124 --> 00:23:14,359
[Number Of Customers So Far: 3 Groups]

444
00:23:14,359 --> 00:23:16,728
[Current Number Of Customers: 0 Groups]

445
00:23:20,265 --> 00:23:22,367
[Why Is No One Coming?]

446
00:23:23,035 --> 00:23:25,404
If the afternoon is just as quiet,

447
00:23:25,404 --> 00:23:28,173
maybe I should go to the village hall
and hand out baked goods.

448
00:23:28,173 --> 00:23:30,309
- Door-to-door sales?
- Yeah.

449
00:23:30,309 --> 00:23:32,211
- Make house calls?
- Yeah, I could go to them.

450
00:23:32,211 --> 00:23:34,112
If things don't pick up this afternoon.

451
00:23:34,112 --> 00:23:35,214
[While Seon Ho Gets Anxious]

452
00:23:35,214 --> 00:23:36,882
But I'm sure someone will come.

453
00:23:36,882 --> 00:23:37,783
You know...

454
00:23:37,783 --> 00:23:39,302
- Seniors!
- Here they come.

455
00:23:40,619 --> 00:23:43,099
I think we've got back-to-back customers.

456
00:23:43,755 --> 00:23:45,353
Here they come.

457
00:23:46,024 --> 00:23:48,293
We've got back-to-back customers.

458
00:23:48,293 --> 00:23:50,736
What took them so long?

459
00:23:52,397 --> 00:23:53,765
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

460
00:23:53,765 --> 00:23:55,634
- You really came.
- Hello.

461
00:23:55,634 --> 00:23:57,069
- Thank you.
- We're back again.

462
00:23:57,069 --> 00:23:58,570
- You came back.
- Thank you.

463
00:23:58,570 --> 00:24:00,539
- Sit anywhere you like.
- This way?

464
00:24:00,539 --> 00:24:02,341
- Hello.
- We're back again.

465
00:24:02,341 --> 00:24:03,675
Thank you.

466
00:24:03,675 --> 00:24:06,311
[As The Long-Awaited Customers Arrive,
They Can't Help But Smile]

467
00:24:06,879 --> 00:24:09,448
You have no idea how happy I am
that you actually came.

468
00:24:09,448 --> 00:24:12,251
Of course, I'm such a big fan of yours.

469
00:24:14,319 --> 00:24:16,688
I've been a fan of yours
since <i>2 Days &amp; 1 Night</i>.

470
00:24:16,688 --> 00:24:18,857
Thank you.

471
00:24:18,857 --> 00:24:20,723
Let me shake your hand.

472
00:24:21,860 --> 00:24:24,280
Why is your hand so cold?

473
00:24:27,566 --> 00:24:29,935
[The Flowers Have Changed]

474
00:24:31,303 --> 00:24:32,754
It's a senior gentleman.

475
00:24:34,439 --> 00:24:35,874
Welcome.

476
00:24:38,677 --> 00:24:41,040
No one is here.

477
00:24:42,748 --> 00:24:45,068
[More Customers Are On The Way]
They're suddenly pouring in.

478
00:24:47,352 --> 00:24:48,520
Welcome.

479
00:24:48,520 --> 00:24:50,422
Do we need to wait?

480
00:24:50,422 --> 00:24:52,391
- You can come in.
- Really?

481
00:24:52,391 --> 00:24:53,792
- Should I take that?
- Yes.

482
00:24:53,792 --> 00:24:55,093
- Hello.
- Hello.

483
00:24:55,093 --> 00:24:57,195
- Welcome.
- Are you a party of three?

484
00:24:57,195 --> 00:24:59,264
Why aren't they coming?

485
00:25:00,999 --> 00:25:02,034
Jeez.

486
00:25:02,034 --> 00:25:03,635
When are they coming?

487
00:25:04,536 --> 00:25:06,138
Hello?

488
00:25:06,138 --> 00:25:08,194
Hurry up.

489
00:25:09,276 --> 00:25:10,951
Where are you?

490
00:25:11,610 --> 00:25:13,312
[Who Is He Waiting For?]

491
00:25:13,312 --> 00:25:14,808
All right.

492
00:25:16,081 --> 00:25:17,916
We've got more customers.

493
00:25:17,916 --> 00:25:19,051
There are more people.

494
00:25:19,051 --> 00:25:21,264
I think they're one big group.

495
00:25:22,955 --> 00:25:24,222
Did you want to come in?

496
00:25:24,222 --> 00:25:26,758
Welcome! Come on in.

497
00:25:26,758 --> 00:25:29,461
[Hello]
Are you the 1 p.m. reservation group?

498
00:25:29,461 --> 00:25:31,530
- Hello.
- Hello.

499
00:25:31,530 --> 00:25:32,931
[The 1 p.m. Customers Have Arrived]

500
00:25:34,900 --> 00:25:37,903
[They Are On Their Way Back
From Exercising At The Health Center]

501
00:25:37,903 --> 00:25:39,771
- Squeeze in.
- There aren't enough seats.

502
00:25:39,771 --> 00:25:41,740
- Are you all together?
- Yes.

503
00:25:41,740 --> 00:25:43,475
[Here's The Table For 4]
Come this way.

504
00:25:43,475 --> 00:25:45,811
Those with sturdy legs can stay standing.

505
00:25:45,811 --> 00:25:47,946
[Village Local's Sense Of Humor]

506
00:25:48,380 --> 00:25:50,682
- Sit here.
- Take a seat.

507
00:25:50,682 --> 00:25:51,750
Have a seat.

508
00:25:51,750 --> 00:25:52,751
On that side...

509
00:25:52,751 --> 00:25:55,187
[The Bakery Quickly Fills Up
With Local Seniors]

510
00:25:55,187 --> 00:25:56,855
I'm doing well.

511
00:25:59,057 --> 00:26:01,426
How do we order?

512
00:26:01,426 --> 00:26:03,161
Are you a doctor?
Why are you wearing a gown?

513
00:26:03,161 --> 00:26:05,323
- I work at the local clinic.
- I see.

514
00:26:06,765 --> 00:26:11,269
[The Seniors Exercise For 1 Hour Every Week
At The Local Clinic]

515
00:26:11,269 --> 00:26:12,938
Now, turn sideways.

516
00:26:15,607 --> 00:26:18,097
Should I call my husband?

517
00:26:20,045 --> 00:26:22,147
Since we serve bread here,

518
00:26:22,147 --> 00:26:24,182
[Biggest Group So Far]
wipe your hands with these warm towels.

519
00:26:24,182 --> 00:26:26,184
Give some to them in there.

520
00:26:26,184 --> 00:26:27,886
- Oh, you already got a menu.
- Thank you.

521
00:26:27,886 --> 00:26:29,121
Three financiers,

522
00:26:29,121 --> 00:26:31,056
[Seon Ho Puts In The Group Order]
and six orangeades.

523
00:26:31,056 --> 00:26:32,657
- Orangeade?
- Yes.

524
00:26:33,392 --> 00:26:34,526
[Chuckle]

525
00:26:34,526 --> 00:26:36,661
[The Large Order Has Brightened Him Up]
And then...

526
00:26:36,661 --> 00:26:38,430
One hot Americano.

527
00:26:41,166 --> 00:26:43,368
Should I make three orangeades?

528
00:26:43,368 --> 00:26:46,104
- Yes, we need to make six in total.
- Okay.

529
00:26:46,104 --> 00:26:48,040
- Thank you.
- Take your time.

530
00:26:48,040 --> 00:26:49,447
Thirty.

531
00:26:50,575 --> 00:26:53,011
[Joo Bin Measures Out The Orange Juice]

532
00:26:54,579 --> 00:26:57,182
[Hee Ae Adds The Ice]

533
00:26:58,250 --> 00:27:01,386
[The Sparkling Water Is Added At The End]

534
00:27:01,386 --> 00:27:03,388
Let's get two of each.
The croissant and the financier.

535
00:27:03,388 --> 00:27:05,505
- Just two each.
- Okay, and the ades.

536
00:27:06,324 --> 00:27:09,461
You don't want me to spend too much?

537
00:27:09,461 --> 00:27:11,997
[It's My Treat Today]
This is a special occasion.

538
00:27:11,997 --> 00:27:15,267
- Two croissants and two financiers.
- And four ades.

539
00:27:15,267 --> 00:27:16,581
No, I mean five.

540
00:27:17,302 --> 00:27:18,637
- How many ades?
- Five, please.

541
00:27:18,637 --> 00:27:19,905
- Five?
- Yes.

542
00:27:19,905 --> 00:27:21,706
We got five more ade orders.

543
00:27:21,706 --> 00:27:23,175
We need to make 11 in total.

544
00:27:23,175 --> 00:27:25,210
- A total of 11 ades?
- Yes.

545
00:27:25,210 --> 00:27:26,711
Okay.

546
00:27:28,113 --> 00:27:29,014
Ninety.

547
00:27:29,014 --> 00:27:31,850
Okay, let's deliver these six first.

548
00:27:31,850 --> 00:27:33,085
We don't need to rush.

549
00:27:33,085 --> 00:27:34,986
- Is he Kim Seon Ho?
- What?

550
00:27:34,986 --> 00:27:37,689
- He's Kim Seon Ho, right?
- Yeah.

551
00:27:37,689 --> 00:27:40,225
[Kim Seon Ho's The Hot Topic Of Conversation]

552
00:27:40,225 --> 00:27:41,993
- He said the place was empty...
- What?

553
00:27:41,993 --> 00:27:44,896
He was upset there were no customers.

554
00:27:44,896 --> 00:27:48,467
He was worried word had spread
that the desserts weren't tasty.

555
00:27:48,467 --> 00:27:51,703
They have to serve all ages
to get more business.

556
00:27:51,703 --> 00:27:53,138
- Isn't that right?
- That's right.

557
00:27:53,138 --> 00:27:54,906
They need to be open to all customers

558
00:27:54,906 --> 00:27:58,310
since there aren't many of us seniors.

559
00:27:59,177 --> 00:28:02,114
[As They Worry About The Young Bakery Staff]

560
00:28:02,514 --> 00:28:04,716
[3 <i>Bokbunja</i> Madeleines,
5 Financiers, 2 <i>Bokbunja</i> Croissants]

561
00:28:04,716 --> 00:28:06,118
[11 Orangeades, 1 Hot Americano]

562
00:28:06,118 --> 00:28:08,987
[The Desserts Are Ready For The Clinic Group]

563
00:28:09,521 --> 00:28:13,492
[But Still Need To Make 5 More Orangeades]

564
00:28:13,492 --> 00:28:15,413
Add the sparkling water.

565
00:28:18,296 --> 00:28:20,999
[Due To Hee Ae And Joo Bin's Teamwork]

566
00:28:24,436 --> 00:28:26,438
[The Ades Are Made Without A Hitch]

567
00:28:27,539 --> 00:28:29,774
[Orders Are Served]
Excuse me.

568
00:28:29,774 --> 00:28:31,209
Those drinks look tasty.

569
00:28:31,209 --> 00:28:33,078
- Don't they look tasty?
- Absolutely.

570
00:28:33,078 --> 00:28:35,647
I've divided it nicely for everyone.

571
00:28:35,647 --> 00:28:37,215
Pass that over.

572
00:28:37,215 --> 00:28:38,884
It's crisp on the outside and soft inside.

573
00:28:38,884 --> 00:28:41,720
Isn't there a dipping sauce?

574
00:28:41,720 --> 00:28:44,322
- It's plenty sweet.
- Enjoy it with a drink.

575
00:28:44,322 --> 00:28:45,757
- It goes well with a drink.
- It's sweet.

576
00:28:45,757 --> 00:28:47,893
- Have these together?
- That's right.

577
00:28:47,893 --> 00:28:49,327
Thank you for the food.

578
00:28:50,228 --> 00:28:51,885
[Feeling Unsure]
Let's see.

579
00:28:53,098 --> 00:28:57,869
[He Dips It In]

580
00:28:57,869 --> 00:29:00,138
[Oh, Dear]

581
00:29:01,606 --> 00:29:04,876
I'm just a country man.
I don't know how to eat this.

582
00:29:05,911 --> 00:29:08,313
Just bite this and sip that.

583
00:29:08,313 --> 00:29:10,148
There's nothing to it.

584
00:29:10,148 --> 00:29:11,416
That's it.

585
00:29:13,585 --> 00:29:17,856
You live long enough,
and you get to try food like this.

586
00:29:17,856 --> 00:29:20,358
It's a good thing you've lived this long.

587
00:29:20,358 --> 00:29:22,894
- Yes.
- You're right.

588
00:29:22,894 --> 00:29:25,230
[The Director Checks On The Seniors]
Cut it into pieces and share it.

589
00:29:25,230 --> 00:29:26,698
- Should I cut it for you?
- Yes.

590
00:29:26,698 --> 00:29:28,133
[At The Other Table]

591
00:29:28,133 --> 00:29:30,735
It's big enough to share.

592
00:29:33,972 --> 00:29:36,174
We'll do it ourselves. Go and eat.

593
00:29:36,942 --> 00:29:38,204
Here you go.

594
00:29:38,896 --> 00:29:41,980
- Have fun, ladies.
- All right.

595
00:29:41,980 --> 00:29:42,981
[Have A Good Time]

596
00:29:42,981 --> 00:29:44,149
Thank you.

597
00:29:45,917 --> 00:29:47,886
It's tasty.

598
00:29:47,886 --> 00:29:50,255
It's nice and sweet.

599
00:29:52,390 --> 00:29:54,960
[Nice And Refreshing]

600
00:29:55,360 --> 00:29:57,255
- Is it good?
- Yes.

601
00:29:57,829 --> 00:30:01,132
Thank you for coming.

602
00:30:01,132 --> 00:30:03,902
- Let's make a heart.
- One, two, three!

603
00:30:06,738 --> 00:30:08,406
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

604
00:30:08,406 --> 00:30:10,442
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

605
00:30:17,249 --> 00:30:19,651
Having extra hands makes a big difference.

606
00:30:19,651 --> 00:30:22,161
We handled all those orders so quickly.

607
00:30:31,029 --> 00:30:32,998
What time is it?

608
00:30:32,998 --> 00:30:35,533
[1:30 p.m.]

609
00:30:39,137 --> 00:30:42,507
[What's For Lunch Today?]

610
00:30:42,507 --> 00:30:44,387
Is it lunchtime?

611
00:30:45,644 --> 00:30:47,045
What are you cooking?

612
00:30:47,045 --> 00:30:48,113
Musubi.

613
00:30:48,113 --> 00:30:49,581
[Today's Lunch Is Musubi]

614
00:30:49,581 --> 00:30:52,450
[Hawaiian-Style Rice Balls
Wrapped In Seaweed]

615
00:30:52,450 --> 00:30:55,253
[Today's Special Is Chef Cha-Style Musubi]

616
00:30:55,854 --> 00:30:56,921
[Chef Cha's Tip]

617
00:30:56,921 --> 00:30:59,257
[Simmer Ham In Oyster Sauce And Soy Sauce
To Enhance Flavor]

618
00:30:59,257 --> 00:31:01,693
I'm just one short of fitting them all in.

619
00:31:01,693 --> 00:31:03,495
[Just One Slice Of Ham Left]
I was so close.

620
00:31:03,495 --> 00:31:05,730
[It May Look Thrown Together]
I was aiming to fit them all in.

621
00:31:05,730 --> 00:31:08,667
[But It's All Carefully Planned]
You have to cut them precisely.

622
00:31:12,971 --> 00:31:15,707
[Cook The Ham In A Sweet And Salty Sauce]

623
00:31:16,441 --> 00:31:19,611
[Then Prepares The Egg Garnish]

624
00:31:20,211 --> 00:31:22,947
[Cook Them On Low Heat]

625
00:31:23,515 --> 00:31:26,384
[To Get A Hearty Egg Garnish]

626
00:31:28,153 --> 00:31:30,322
[Rice Cooker Open]

627
00:31:38,129 --> 00:31:41,700
[Add Sesame Oil, Salt, And Sesame Seeds
To The Well-Cooked Rice]

628
00:31:46,404 --> 00:31:48,340
[Chef Cha's Musubi Mold Brought From Home]

629
00:31:49,674 --> 00:31:52,110
[The Mold Is Placed On The Roasted Seaweed]

630
00:31:53,712 --> 00:31:55,613
[Add Rice]

631
00:31:55,613 --> 00:31:57,882
[Ham]

632
00:31:57,882 --> 00:32:00,018
[Egg]

633
00:32:00,018 --> 00:32:02,654
[Top It With More Rice And Wrap It Up]

634
00:32:09,894 --> 00:32:10,895
- Coat it.
- Okay.

635
00:32:12,897 --> 00:32:15,600
That's it. It's looking good.

636
00:32:15,600 --> 00:32:17,102
- Good job.
- Thank you.

637
00:32:19,738 --> 00:32:22,807
[Brush On Some Sesame Oil]

638
00:32:24,342 --> 00:32:27,345
[Cut Into Neat Slices]

639
00:32:27,345 --> 00:32:29,114
Okay, it's ready.

640
00:32:29,114 --> 00:32:32,183
[Chef Cha's Sweet And Savory
Musubi Is Complete]

641
00:32:32,183 --> 00:32:34,719
- Can I try an end piece?
- Go ahead.

642
00:32:35,954 --> 00:32:37,607
Give it a taste. How is it?

643
00:32:38,542 --> 00:32:39,657
It's amazing.

644
00:32:39,657 --> 00:32:41,126
- Amazing?
- Yes.

645
00:32:41,126 --> 00:32:43,194
- It's so good.
- That's good to hear.

646
00:32:43,194 --> 00:32:46,598
[Time To Prepare The Next Dish
To Serve With The Musubi]

647
00:32:47,098 --> 00:32:51,536
[He Takes Out Handfuls Of Crisp Beansprouts]

648
00:32:51,536 --> 00:32:54,339
[And Washes Them Cleanly]

649
00:32:57,075 --> 00:32:58,143
Put it on here.

650
00:32:58,143 --> 00:33:00,712
[It's The Kimchi They Got
From The Senior Who Lives Next Door]

651
00:33:00,712 --> 00:33:05,250
[Jeolla-Style Kimchi With The Rich,
Homemade Flavor Of A Mother's Touch]

652
00:33:05,650 --> 00:33:09,988
[It's So Packed With Ingredients
That The Kimchi Alone Is A Dish In Itself]

653
00:33:09,988 --> 00:33:12,023
[Red Chili Powder]

654
00:33:12,023 --> 00:33:14,025
[Anchovy Fish Sauce]

655
00:33:16,060 --> 00:33:18,830
[Finish With Chili Peppers And Scallions]

656
00:33:24,202 --> 00:33:26,271
[The Spicy Aged-Kimchi Beansprout Stew
Is Complete]

657
00:33:26,271 --> 00:33:28,424
Hang on. One more thing.

658
00:33:29,140 --> 00:33:31,161
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

659
00:33:31,161 --> 00:33:32,383
- Thank you.
- Bye.

660
00:33:32,383 --> 00:33:33,711
- Thank you.
- Goodbye.

661
00:33:33,711 --> 00:33:35,711
[The Hall Team Wrap Up The Morning Shift]
Take care.

662
00:33:37,582 --> 00:33:39,350
All right.

663
00:33:40,652 --> 00:33:43,822
[Break Time]

664
00:33:43,822 --> 00:33:45,490
Let's eat.

665
00:33:45,490 --> 00:33:47,358
It looks so good.

666
00:33:48,059 --> 00:33:49,861
- We should have taken photos
- I'll do it.

667
00:33:49,861 --> 00:33:52,096
- But I forgot.
- All of the meals?

668
00:33:52,096 --> 00:33:53,231
- What a shame.
- I know.

669
00:33:53,231 --> 00:33:54,666
We only took a photo in the first week,

670
00:33:54,666 --> 00:33:56,901
- then we started eating in a rush.
- Right?

671
00:33:56,901 --> 00:34:00,271
The kimchi stew, soybean paste stew,
and curry were all delicious.

672
00:34:00,271 --> 00:34:03,374
[You'll Be Just As Impressed Today]

673
00:34:04,175 --> 00:34:06,749
- Thank you for the meal.
- Thank you!

674
00:34:18,223 --> 00:34:19,676
It's so refreshing.

675
00:34:24,762 --> 00:34:26,197
It's so tasty.

676
00:34:29,801 --> 00:34:32,837
[Does It Taste Okay?]

677
00:34:32,837 --> 00:34:34,672
This stew is delicious.

678
00:34:35,340 --> 00:34:36,474
It's so good.

679
00:34:36,474 --> 00:34:40,326
I noticed he seasoned the ham.

680
00:34:40,326 --> 00:34:43,314
[Let's Try The Musubi]

681
00:34:50,955 --> 00:34:53,291
It's better than the one I had in Hawaii.

682
00:34:53,291 --> 00:34:55,238
- Does it taste okay?
- Yes.

683
00:34:56,828 --> 00:35:01,733
[Musubi And Beansprout Combo]

684
00:35:02,200 --> 00:35:03,968
[A Sip Of Stew]

685
00:35:03,968 --> 00:35:06,738
[A Bite Of Musubi]

686
00:35:07,138 --> 00:35:08,606
[Joo Bin Is Also Impressed
By Chef Cha's Cooking]

687
00:35:08,606 --> 00:35:10,341
It's so tasty.

688
00:35:10,341 --> 00:35:13,192
Do you wrap it up
and slice it like <i>gimbap</i>?

689
00:35:13,678 --> 00:35:14,946
- Mold.
- You used a mold?

690
00:35:14,946 --> 00:35:16,469
[He Brought It Himself]
I used a mold.

691
00:35:19,684 --> 00:35:21,452
You must be tired
from putting this all together.

692
00:35:21,452 --> 00:35:22,820
I'm fine.

693
00:35:22,820 --> 00:35:24,756
Ki Taek helped me.

694
00:35:26,224 --> 00:35:29,661
[Only One Musubi Left]

695
00:35:29,661 --> 00:35:31,095
Who wants this?

696
00:35:31,095 --> 00:35:33,331
The younglings should...

697
00:35:33,331 --> 00:35:35,133
- You should...
- He's a youngling.

698
00:35:35,133 --> 00:35:36,868
You should have it, Hee Ae.

699
00:35:36,868 --> 00:35:39,404
Eat up. You need more fuel for your build.

700
00:35:39,404 --> 00:35:42,140
Eat when your elder offers you food.

701
00:35:42,140 --> 00:35:43,441
Yes, sir.

702
00:35:43,441 --> 00:35:45,410
[If You Insist...]

703
00:35:45,410 --> 00:35:48,172
[Joking Around]
Joo Bin wanted it, but I gave it to you.

704
00:35:48,172 --> 00:35:50,749
I'd have given it to Joo Bin.

705
00:35:50,749 --> 00:35:51,850
[Can I Really Eat This?]

706
00:35:51,850 --> 00:35:54,221
I'm just kidding. Go ahead and eat.

707
00:35:54,986 --> 00:35:57,422
I'm just kidding. Go ahead and eat.

708
00:35:57,808 --> 00:36:02,961
[I'll Work Even Harder
To Make Up For Taking Joo Bin's Portion]

709
00:36:02,961 --> 00:36:05,363
- You need to make another item, right?
- Of course.

710
00:36:05,363 --> 00:36:07,799
[A New Dessert For This Afternoon]

711
00:36:07,799 --> 00:36:09,701
See those petals?

712
00:36:09,701 --> 00:36:14,172
That's the most difficult dessert to make.

713
00:36:14,172 --> 00:36:17,351
- Thank you for the meal.
- It was delicious.

714
00:36:19,077 --> 00:36:20,411
[Bonjour Bakery]

715
00:36:20,411 --> 00:36:21,479
- Joo Bin.
- Yes?

716
00:36:21,479 --> 00:36:24,582
We have a new afternoon menu.

717
00:36:25,150 --> 00:36:26,250
Brown rice...

718
00:36:26,250 --> 00:36:27,752
[Keeping An Eye Out For Seniors]

719
00:36:27,752 --> 00:36:29,587
Yuzu...

720
00:36:29,587 --> 00:36:34,258
Saint-Honoré.

721
00:36:35,026 --> 00:36:37,328
[Today's New Signature Dessert]

722
00:36:37,328 --> 00:36:40,298
[Bonjour Bakery]

723
00:36:41,265 --> 00:36:42,967
[Saint-Honoré]

724
00:36:42,967 --> 00:36:45,903
[The Ultimate Expression
Of French Pastry Craftsmanship]

725
00:36:46,738 --> 00:36:50,241
[Brown Rice Yuzu Saint-Honoré]

726
00:36:50,808 --> 00:36:52,910
I'd better keep one of these for later.

727
00:36:53,511 --> 00:36:55,580
I really want to try this one.

728
00:36:55,580 --> 00:36:59,291
He said it was hard to make,
but it turned out beautiful.

729
00:37:01,552 --> 00:37:05,156
[It's A Hit With The Staff Members]

730
00:37:10,862 --> 00:37:12,566
We have a customer.

731
00:37:12,566 --> 00:37:14,387
Come on in.

732
00:37:14,766 --> 00:37:16,868
- I want to buy some bread.
- Hello.

733
00:37:17,502 --> 00:37:19,345
What would you recommend?

734
00:37:25,212 --> 00:37:28,646
I had kouign-amann this morning,
and it was delicious.

735
00:37:28,646 --> 00:37:30,648
I'll take one.

736
00:37:30,648 --> 00:37:33,217
- What's this one?
- It's called a croissant,

737
00:37:33,217 --> 00:37:34,852
and it's filled with <i>bokbunja</i> jam.

738
00:37:34,852 --> 00:37:37,255
- I'll take that one as well.
- Okay.

739
00:37:37,255 --> 00:37:40,525
One kouign-amann and one croissant.

740
00:37:40,525 --> 00:37:42,260
I'll take this, that, and this one.

741
00:37:42,260 --> 00:37:43,861
I'll take this, that, and this one.

742
00:37:43,861 --> 00:37:44,896
What's this one?

743
00:37:44,896 --> 00:37:46,698
It's a yuzu madeleine.
That one's also delicious.

744
00:37:46,698 --> 00:37:47,932
Give me one of everything.

745
00:37:47,932 --> 00:37:50,101
Okay, Green Barley Tart...

746
00:37:51,069 --> 00:37:52,704
Welcome.

747
00:37:52,704 --> 00:37:54,038
We came to buy bread.

748
00:37:54,038 --> 00:37:55,440
We have bread over there.

749
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:56,839
Welcome.

750
00:37:57,742 --> 00:37:58,810
Hello.

751
00:37:58,810 --> 00:38:00,313
- All the best.
- Welcome!

752
00:38:01,079 --> 00:38:02,680
How many people?

753
00:38:02,680 --> 00:38:03,748
No, I'm buying them to go.

754
00:38:03,748 --> 00:38:05,183
- Hey.
- What?

755
00:38:05,183 --> 00:38:06,517
What are you doing?

756
00:38:06,517 --> 00:38:08,433
- They're returning customers.
- This one?

757
00:38:11,389 --> 00:38:12,523
These three.

758
00:38:12,523 --> 00:38:14,592
Okay, place them there.

759
00:38:14,592 --> 00:38:16,360
One moment.

760
00:38:16,360 --> 00:38:17,714
How much is it?

761
00:38:18,896 --> 00:38:20,064
It's 12,000 won.

762
00:38:20,064 --> 00:38:21,232
Hand over 2,000 won.

763
00:38:21,232 --> 00:38:22,322
"Hand over."

764
00:38:23,568 --> 00:38:25,670
Buy another one.

765
00:38:25,670 --> 00:38:27,305
[We Already Got A Lot]
How much is it?

766
00:38:27,305 --> 00:38:29,040
I have the money.

767
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:30,141
How much is one roll?

768
00:38:30,141 --> 00:38:31,609
I'll give you more money.

769
00:38:31,609 --> 00:38:34,479
[I'll Give You 2,000 Won, Buy More Bread]
No, we're 2,000 won short.

770
00:38:34,479 --> 00:38:36,647
[This Senior]

771
00:38:36,647 --> 00:38:38,416
[Was Here Earlier This Morning]
Someone's coming.

772
00:38:38,416 --> 00:38:39,951
No one is here.

773
00:38:41,753 --> 00:38:43,254
[Looking Around]

774
00:38:45,456 --> 00:38:47,892
Why is no one here?

775
00:38:47,892 --> 00:38:53,030
[He Was Concerned That The Bakery Was Empty]

776
00:38:53,698 --> 00:38:56,033
Their desserts are really tasty.

777
00:38:56,033 --> 00:38:58,669
We can have beef another time.

778
00:38:58,669 --> 00:39:02,106
Turn the car around.

779
00:39:03,708 --> 00:39:07,812
[So He Rushed Back Again In The Afternoon]

780
00:39:07,812 --> 00:39:09,814
- Did you get four?
- Three.

781
00:39:09,814 --> 00:39:12,350
- Three in total. I also packed some jam.
- Okay.

782
00:39:12,350 --> 00:39:13,885
Add one more.

783
00:39:13,885 --> 00:39:17,088
[Stunned]
How many do you plan to buy?

784
00:39:17,822 --> 00:39:20,324
- Are these bread?
- They are.

785
00:39:20,324 --> 00:39:22,193
- These.
- It's bread.

786
00:39:22,193 --> 00:39:26,297
Let's try it and see how it tastes.

787
00:39:26,297 --> 00:39:29,667
Green barley bread, yuzu bread...

788
00:39:30,067 --> 00:39:32,737
[Oh, Sir]

789
00:39:32,737 --> 00:39:34,572
I want to spread the word.

790
00:39:34,572 --> 00:39:37,909
[He Wants To Do What He Can To Help]
I see.

791
00:39:41,445 --> 00:39:42,647
Thank you.

792
00:39:42,647 --> 00:39:44,148
That's enough.

793
00:39:44,148 --> 00:39:46,083
Thank you.

794
00:39:48,286 --> 00:39:49,687
Goodbye.

795
00:40:00,431 --> 00:40:01,632
Hello.

796
00:40:01,632 --> 00:40:02,967
- Hello.
- Hello.

797
00:40:02,967 --> 00:40:05,169
We came back again.

798
00:40:05,169 --> 00:40:06,684
Thank you.

799
00:40:07,205 --> 00:40:09,373
Sit over there, please.

800
00:40:09,373 --> 00:40:12,310
[The Senior He Met This Morning]
Why not drop by our café?

801
00:40:12,310 --> 00:40:13,578
[She Promised To Visit]
I'll come by for a tea later.

802
00:40:13,578 --> 00:40:15,313
A cup of tea?

803
00:40:15,313 --> 00:40:16,681
[And She Kept Her Promise]
Welcome.

804
00:40:16,681 --> 00:40:17,648
You really came.

805
00:40:17,648 --> 00:40:19,813
- Hello.
- Thank you for coming.

806
00:40:20,518 --> 00:40:22,954
[Looking Around]

807
00:40:23,525 --> 00:40:26,090
[Concerned About How Empty The Bakery Was]

808
00:40:27,091 --> 00:40:30,494
[She Came Back For A Second Time Today,
This Time With A Different Company]

809
00:40:30,494 --> 00:40:33,531
[So In Suk, Kim Tae Gyu
From The Neighboring Village]

810
00:40:34,165 --> 00:40:35,569
What was this place before?

811
00:40:35,569 --> 00:40:38,502
It was a corner shop before.

812
00:40:38,502 --> 00:40:41,572
Are they the celebrities?

813
00:40:41,572 --> 00:40:42,807
- That's Kim Hee Ae.
- What?

814
00:40:42,807 --> 00:40:44,275
Kim Hee Ae.

815
00:40:44,275 --> 00:40:45,683
Kim Hee Ae.

816
00:40:46,711 --> 00:40:48,045
[Our Local Bakery's]

817
00:40:48,045 --> 00:40:51,048
[Manager Is Kim Hee Ae]
See the lady with the short hair?

818
00:40:51,048 --> 00:40:52,083
That's Kim Hee Ae.

819
00:40:52,083 --> 00:40:53,517
And inside the kitchen,

820
00:40:53,517 --> 00:40:56,754
Cha Seung Won bakes the desserts.

821
00:40:57,321 --> 00:40:59,624
[Our Local Bakery's]

822
00:40:59,624 --> 00:41:03,127
[Chef Is Cha Seung Won]

823
00:41:03,127 --> 00:41:05,129
Even if we want a slice of bread,

824
00:41:05,129 --> 00:41:07,531
we can hardly get around,

825
00:41:07,531 --> 00:41:09,760
so all the old ladies
in this area are thrilled.

826
00:41:10,735 --> 00:41:13,571
- For seniors...
- They're constantly coming and going.

827
00:41:16,207 --> 00:41:17,875
[It's Time To Make The New Afternoon Item]

828
00:41:17,875 --> 00:41:20,511
The King of Baking.

829
00:41:20,511 --> 00:41:21,511
[By The King Of Baking]

830
00:41:22,146 --> 00:41:23,748
Well...

831
00:41:24,382 --> 00:41:26,517
It's time for the second event.

832
00:41:26,517 --> 00:41:28,352
Introducing Part Two.

833
00:41:29,220 --> 00:41:32,256
Saint-Honoré!

834
00:41:33,090 --> 00:41:34,959
They say it's the hardest dessert to make.

835
00:41:34,959 --> 00:41:37,261
Saint-Honoré.

836
00:41:37,261 --> 00:41:40,531
I'll be taking on a top-tier challenge.

837
00:41:40,531 --> 00:41:42,533
[A Top-Tier Challenge Is Coming Up]
That's the second event of the day.

838
00:41:42,533 --> 00:41:46,437
[But His Hands Are Shaking]
But I've got the shakes.

839
00:41:46,437 --> 00:41:49,373
[From Piping Cream All Morning]

840
00:41:49,774 --> 00:41:51,676
- My hands are shaking.
- Really?

841
00:41:51,676 --> 00:41:53,144
What should I do?

842
00:41:53,144 --> 00:41:55,179
But I can do it.

843
00:41:55,179 --> 00:41:56,547
- Of course.
- Who's the King of Baking?

844
00:41:56,547 --> 00:41:59,517
It's no challenge for the King of Baking.

845
00:41:59,517 --> 00:42:02,486
Nothing can stop me.

846
00:42:02,486 --> 00:42:04,046
Nothing.

847
00:42:04,689 --> 00:42:05,689
[Sighs]

848
00:42:07,358 --> 00:42:09,226
[Without A Doubt, The Most Challenging]

849
00:42:10,328 --> 00:42:13,931
[And The Most Beautiful]

850
00:42:14,532 --> 00:42:17,802
[Named After Saint Honoré,
The Patron Saint Of Pastry Chefs]

851
00:42:17,802 --> 00:42:21,439
[A Dazzling Showcase
Of French Culinary At Its Finest]

852
00:42:21,439 --> 00:42:23,374
[Bonjour Bakery]

853
00:42:24,508 --> 00:42:27,945
[Bonjour Brown Rice Yuzu Saint-Honoré]

854
00:42:29,246 --> 00:42:31,115
[To Create This Timeless Masterpiece]

855
00:42:31,115 --> 00:42:33,217
[The King Of Baking
Must Take On The Challenge]

856
00:42:33,217 --> 00:42:37,722
[Of Three Essential Steps]

857
00:42:38,356 --> 00:42:39,857
[Step 1: Make The Brown Rice Yuzu Crunch]

858
00:42:39,857 --> 00:42:41,692
[Level: Intermediate]

859
00:42:42,893 --> 00:42:46,397
[Yuzu Chocolate Made With Yuzu Juice
Is Melted Over A Hot Water Bath]

860
00:42:47,832 --> 00:42:53,270
[The Soft, Melted Chocolate Is Mixed
With The Toasted Brown Rice]

861
00:42:55,740 --> 00:42:57,375
[Using The Tool Brought Over By Ki Taek]

862
00:42:59,010 --> 00:43:01,712
[He Spreads It Out Flat]

863
00:43:06,150 --> 00:43:09,653
[After Setting It In The Freezer,
He Breaks Them Into Nail-Sized Pieces]

864
00:43:10,421 --> 00:43:11,522
Ki Taek, heat it up.

865
00:43:11,522 --> 00:43:13,057
[Step 2: Make Brown Rice Mousse]
It's 80 degrees, right?

866
00:43:13,057 --> 00:43:14,558
[Level: Advanced]
Yes, I'll make this.

867
00:43:14,558 --> 00:43:15,760
Okay.

868
00:43:16,360 --> 00:43:18,596
[Put Brown Rice Milk, Cream,
And Sugar Into A Saucepan]

869
00:43:18,596 --> 00:43:20,264
[And Stir Until It Reaches 80 Degrees]

870
00:43:21,432 --> 00:43:22,800
[Clink]

871
00:43:23,508 --> 00:43:28,246
[Even With Shaky Hands,
He Has To Whip The Yolk]

872
00:43:30,541 --> 00:43:31,675
That's enough.

873
00:43:31,675 --> 00:43:33,210
[Add The Whipped Yolk To The Milky Base]

874
00:43:33,210 --> 00:43:34,678
[And Whip The Mixture Once More]
More.

875
00:43:34,678 --> 00:43:36,247
Okay.

876
00:43:39,216 --> 00:43:42,086
[Gold Chocolate]

877
00:43:42,086 --> 00:43:44,488
[A Couverture Chocolate]

878
00:43:44,488 --> 00:43:47,458
[That Adds A Buttery-Caramel Flavor
And A Distinctive Golden Color]

879
00:43:48,292 --> 00:43:50,661
The underworld of baking.

880
00:43:50,661 --> 00:43:52,563
[All Of A Sudden?]

881
00:43:52,563 --> 00:43:55,433
"It's the road to hell."

882
00:43:55,433 --> 00:43:56,834
That's where I'm heading now.

883
00:43:56,834 --> 00:43:58,369
[Time To Go Down To Hell]

884
00:43:58,369 --> 00:44:01,439
[The Hell Of Adding The Decoration]

885
00:44:01,439 --> 00:44:03,808
[Fill Molds 30 Percent Full
With Whipped Brown Rice Mousse]

886
00:44:13,717 --> 00:44:16,654
[Each Mold Is Filled Only By 30 Percent]

887
00:44:16,654 --> 00:44:18,422
[To Place This Fellow On Top]

888
00:44:19,123 --> 00:44:21,425
[The Brown Rice Ganache (Chocolate Filling)]

889
00:44:24,495 --> 00:44:28,199
[Add Another Layer Of Brown Rice Mousse]

890
00:44:28,199 --> 00:44:29,767
[For A Smooth Finish]

891
00:44:29,767 --> 00:44:33,037
[Each Mold Is Filled To The Brim]

892
00:44:38,008 --> 00:44:40,411
[Once It Sets In The Freezer]

893
00:44:40,411 --> 00:44:42,780
[They Harden Into Smooth Round Circles]

894
00:44:43,314 --> 00:44:46,317
[And Are Placed Atop
The Pre-Baked Puff Pastry]

895
00:44:52,223 --> 00:44:55,126
[Why Is Ki Taek Suddenly
Making A Cup Of Coffee?]

896
00:44:58,496 --> 00:45:00,297
[So That The King Of Baking
Can Get His Energy Up]

897
00:45:00,297 --> 00:45:03,868
[To Complete The Final Step]
That hits the spot.

898
00:45:04,702 --> 00:45:06,337
[Step 3: Pipe Brown Rice Cream Into Petal Shapes]

899
00:45:06,337 --> 00:45:09,440
[Level: Brutal]

900
00:45:10,174 --> 00:45:11,342
[A Feast For The Eyes]

901
00:45:11,342 --> 00:45:14,178
[Lavish Cream Petals]

902
00:45:14,712 --> 00:45:15,880
[Following The Flowing Contours]

903
00:45:15,880 --> 00:45:19,683
[This Intricate Technique Requires
Perfect Pressure And Rhythm]

904
00:45:19,683 --> 00:45:21,018
[A Few Days Ago In Seoul]
It really...

905
00:45:21,018 --> 00:45:23,754
- You really need good pressure control.
- That's right.

906
00:45:23,754 --> 00:45:24,788
This is the hardest one.

907
00:45:24,788 --> 00:45:26,290
It's the toughest by far.

908
00:45:26,290 --> 00:45:28,359
- This one?
- It's the hardest one I've made.

909
00:45:28,359 --> 00:45:30,895
- Yes, this is the hardest one of all.
- It's the toughest one.

910
00:45:30,895 --> 00:45:33,597
- Don't you think so, Ki Taek?
- Yes.

911
00:45:33,597 --> 00:45:35,232
- It's so hard.
- It's no simple task.

912
00:45:35,232 --> 00:45:36,832
[Tough From The Get-Go]
It's no easy feat.

913
00:45:37,434 --> 00:45:38,869
Let's test it out.

914
00:45:39,470 --> 00:45:43,107
[Carefully Checking The Cream's Consistency]

915
00:45:45,409 --> 00:45:46,644
Okay, we're good to go.

916
00:45:46,644 --> 00:45:47,978
- Okay, I'll bring it over.
- Let's do this.

917
00:45:47,978 --> 00:45:50,481
[It's Crunch Time]

918
00:45:50,481 --> 00:45:52,950
[A Drop Of Cream To Keep It In Place]

919
00:45:55,686 --> 00:45:59,156
[He's Faced Many Challenges So Far]

920
00:45:59,890 --> 00:46:01,725
[But]

921
00:46:01,725 --> 00:46:03,327
[Can He Pull It Off Again?]

922
00:46:04,428 --> 00:46:06,497
[Will It Be Another Happy Ending?]

923
00:46:15,839 --> 00:46:20,344
[Soft Waves Of Brown Rice Cream]

924
00:46:21,078 --> 00:46:23,614
[In Sync With The Rhythm
Of The Rotating Stand]

925
00:46:28,252 --> 00:46:33,157
[An Elegant Shape Coming Together
One Groove At A Time]

926
00:46:46,971 --> 00:46:48,472
[Yuzu Filling]

927
00:46:50,741 --> 00:46:52,076
[Fragrant Gold Beads]

928
00:46:52,076 --> 00:46:55,412
[To Embroider The Cream Petals]

929
00:46:56,380 --> 00:46:59,650
[Add Another Layer Of Cream Petals On Top]

930
00:47:06,090 --> 00:47:09,393
[The Center Is Also Filled With Cream]

931
00:47:11,729 --> 00:47:13,797
[Bite-Sized Caramel Choux Puffs]

932
00:47:14,431 --> 00:47:16,066
[Handmade Brown Rice Yuzu Crunch]

933
00:47:16,066 --> 00:47:18,235
[And Yuzu Filling As Garnish]

934
00:47:26,310 --> 00:47:29,213
Brown Rice Yuzu Sante-Honoré.

935
00:47:29,213 --> 00:47:31,448
Saint-Honoré.

936
00:47:31,448 --> 00:47:33,050
The King of Baking!

937
00:47:33,050 --> 00:47:34,785
- The King of Baking!
- The King of Baking!

938
00:47:34,785 --> 00:47:37,488
- The King of Baking.
- The King of Baking.

939
00:47:37,488 --> 00:47:39,256
Saint-Honoré.

940
00:47:39,256 --> 00:47:43,494
[Did You See My Handmade
Pinnacle Of Beauty?]

941
00:47:43,494 --> 00:47:45,496
[Take A Look]

942
00:47:45,496 --> 00:47:47,965
[Applause]

943
00:47:47,965 --> 00:47:49,700
The King of Baking!

944
00:47:49,700 --> 00:47:55,105
- The King of Baking!
- The King of Baking!

945
00:47:55,105 --> 00:47:56,974
[Look How Happy He Is]

946
00:47:56,974 --> 00:47:57,974
Gosh.

947
00:47:58,676 --> 00:48:00,577
Isn't it amazing?

948
00:48:00,577 --> 00:48:03,714
I feel good about it. What a relief.

949
00:48:03,714 --> 00:48:04,954
My goodness.

950
00:48:04,954 --> 00:48:06,750
I feel so proud.

951
00:48:06,750 --> 00:48:08,852
I bet you didn't think I could do it.
Be honest.

952
00:48:08,852 --> 00:48:12,890
[No, We Knew You Would Pull It Off]

953
00:48:13,957 --> 00:48:16,560
[Through The Countless Challenges]

954
00:48:16,560 --> 00:48:20,804
[The King Of Baking Has Steadily Evolved]

955
00:48:20,804 --> 00:48:21,899
I need to...

956
00:48:21,899 --> 00:48:23,367
[Over The Last Few Days]

957
00:48:23,367 --> 00:48:24,902
[He Hasn't Messed Up The Cream Petals Once]
That's perfect.

958
00:48:24,902 --> 00:48:26,670
- This is how you do it.
- Yes.

959
00:48:26,670 --> 00:48:29,705
- I've got it. I think I can do it.
- Yes.

960
00:48:30,941 --> 00:48:33,510
[He Even Kept Visualizing It In His Head]

961
00:48:33,510 --> 00:48:36,914
Pressure control.

962
00:48:49,026 --> 00:48:51,028
I am the supreme master!

963
00:48:51,028 --> 00:48:53,364
[As His Confidence Grew]

964
00:48:54,832 --> 00:48:59,103
[His Flowers Grew Even More Beautiful]

965
00:49:09,980 --> 00:49:11,348
[King Of Baking]

966
00:49:11,348 --> 00:49:14,151
I'm the King of Baking.

967
00:49:15,119 --> 00:49:17,087
[Technically Speaking]

968
00:49:17,087 --> 00:49:21,191
[The Saint-Honoré
Falls Under Pastries, Not Baking]

969
00:49:22,226 --> 00:49:25,729
[4:30 p.m.]

970
00:49:26,764 --> 00:49:29,133
[Bonjour Bakery]

971
00:49:29,133 --> 00:49:31,402
[The Regular Local Customers]

972
00:49:31,402 --> 00:49:33,737
[Have Come To The Bakery Again]

973
00:49:35,038 --> 00:49:37,441
[Parking Area]

974
00:49:39,143 --> 00:49:42,546
[Precise Parking]

975
00:49:42,946 --> 00:49:44,081
Hello.

976
00:49:44,081 --> 00:49:45,349
Welcome.

977
00:49:50,020 --> 00:49:51,889
- You want to browse first?
- Yeah.

978
00:49:51,889 --> 00:49:53,223
You want to take a look?

979
00:49:53,624 --> 00:49:54,624
Here.

980
00:49:55,526 --> 00:49:56,994
Ma'am.

981
00:49:56,994 --> 00:50:00,464
Wait one moment. Browse around.

982
00:50:01,098 --> 00:50:02,366
Is this also bread?

983
00:50:02,366 --> 00:50:04,301
Yeah, it's all bread.

984
00:50:04,301 --> 00:50:05,369
No, it's not.

985
00:50:05,969 --> 00:50:07,771
[Is It Real Or Fake?]
Yes, it is!

986
00:50:07,771 --> 00:50:09,173
- It's just...
- It's bread.

987
00:50:09,173 --> 00:50:11,375
- It's just a model.
- Really?

988
00:50:11,375 --> 00:50:13,944
It's fake. It's not for sale.

989
00:50:13,944 --> 00:50:15,646
It's hard to tell.

990
00:50:15,646 --> 00:50:17,948
[How Funny]
It's just for display.

991
00:50:21,084 --> 00:50:23,220
[Now, The Seniors Come To The Bakery]

992
00:50:23,220 --> 00:50:26,089
[As Part Of Their Daily Routine]

993
00:50:30,661 --> 00:50:31,995
- I'm just here to buy some to go.
- Okay.

994
00:50:31,995 --> 00:50:34,765
Sure. You need to wait a little.

995
00:50:34,765 --> 00:50:36,066
Come and wait here.

996
00:50:36,066 --> 00:50:38,435
[All The Seats Are Taken]
You should sit down while you wait.

997
00:50:38,435 --> 00:50:40,001
I'll come later, then.

998
00:50:40,945 --> 00:50:43,774
[The Ever-Reliable Kim Seon Ho]
I can come back again.

999
00:50:43,774 --> 00:50:46,410
It's not easy going back and forth.

1000
00:50:46,410 --> 00:50:47,511
I'm fine.

1001
00:50:47,511 --> 00:50:49,646
There are no seats.

1002
00:50:49,646 --> 00:50:50,781
Ma'am.

1003
00:50:50,781 --> 00:50:52,216
Sit here a moment.

1004
00:50:52,216 --> 00:50:53,317
Take a seat.

1005
00:50:53,317 --> 00:50:55,652
Wait here. I'll be back in a flash.

1006
00:50:55,652 --> 00:50:57,654
I'll wrap it up before you know it.

1007
00:50:57,654 --> 00:50:59,456
[He Quickly Brought Over A Spare Seat]

1008
00:50:59,456 --> 00:51:01,425
It's busy today.

1009
00:51:01,425 --> 00:51:02,626
Should we come back later?

1010
00:51:02,626 --> 00:51:05,400
- We can buy it tomorrow.
- That's right.

1011
00:51:05,863 --> 00:51:08,031
- We live in the area,
- We'll get them next time?

1012
00:51:08,031 --> 00:51:10,434
So we'll come back another time.

1013
00:51:10,434 --> 00:51:12,536
You're leaving? Just wait a moment.

1014
00:51:12,536 --> 00:51:14,771
- Yes.
- You're busy, so we'll come back later.

1015
00:51:14,771 --> 00:51:16,940
- Don't tire yourself like that.
- No, it's fine.

1016
00:51:16,940 --> 00:51:18,883
Just stay seated
since you're already here.

1017
00:51:21,512 --> 00:51:23,680
We're not in a rush
since we're only picking up bread.

1018
00:51:23,680 --> 00:51:25,749
Yes, it's better to look around here.

1019
00:51:25,749 --> 00:51:27,818
- What will you do at home?
- We get to look at her.

1020
00:51:27,818 --> 00:51:29,717
Exactly.

1021
00:51:29,717 --> 00:51:32,389
We get to look at this pretty face.

1022
00:51:32,389 --> 00:51:34,558
Thank you.

1023
00:51:34,558 --> 00:51:37,628
Isn't it better to be here than at home?

1024
00:51:37,628 --> 00:51:38,629
[She Tries To Make Them Feel Comfortable]

1025
00:51:38,629 --> 00:51:41,865
I was going to come tomorrow,
but I ended up coming today.

1026
00:51:41,865 --> 00:51:43,033
It was the right call.

1027
00:51:43,033 --> 00:51:46,403
Come today, come tomorrow, come every day.

1028
00:51:46,403 --> 00:51:49,006
Am I supposed to eat bread every day?

1029
00:51:49,006 --> 00:51:52,258
This isn't an everyday kind of place.

1030
00:51:54,444 --> 00:51:56,880
[After Quickly Handling The Previous Orders]

1031
00:51:56,880 --> 00:51:58,215
All right.

1032
00:51:58,215 --> 00:52:00,584
What would you like me to wrap up for you?

1033
00:52:00,584 --> 00:52:02,679
I'll get this one today
and a loaf of bread tomorrow.

1034
00:52:02,679 --> 00:52:04,200
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

1035
00:52:04,200 --> 00:52:06,957
One each? One, two, three, four.

1036
00:52:06,957 --> 00:52:08,400
Four in total.

1037
00:52:09,626 --> 00:52:11,261
Okay, put them on the counter.

1038
00:52:11,261 --> 00:52:13,063
I'll wrap them up nicely for you.

1039
00:52:13,063 --> 00:52:14,164
You don't need to wrap them up.

1040
00:52:14,164 --> 00:52:16,767
I need to put them in a pretty package.

1041
00:52:16,767 --> 00:52:19,269
[Feels Bad About Taking Another Bag]
We have a standard to uphold.

1042
00:52:19,269 --> 00:52:21,605
You don't have to put it in there.

1043
00:52:21,605 --> 00:52:22,773
You don't have to.

1044
00:52:22,773 --> 00:52:25,642
- I'll just take...
- I have to because that's the rule.

1045
00:52:25,642 --> 00:52:27,544
I'm just a part-timer.
The manager will scold me if I don't.

1046
00:52:27,544 --> 00:52:29,098
You're a part-time employee?

1047
00:52:29,947 --> 00:52:30,847
You're such a talker.

1048
00:52:30,847 --> 00:52:32,950
I'll get a loaf of bread tomorrow.

1049
00:52:32,950 --> 00:52:35,476
You already bought this,
and you're going to spend more?

1050
00:52:37,421 --> 00:52:40,457
[A Generous Bundle Of Jam]

1051
00:52:40,457 --> 00:52:42,292
One for each of you.

1052
00:52:42,292 --> 00:52:44,227
Here you go.

1053
00:52:44,227 --> 00:52:46,129
Hold on.

1054
00:52:46,129 --> 00:52:48,028
There you go, ma'am.

1055
00:52:49,700 --> 00:52:52,436
- What about the loaf of bread?
- They're making it tomorrow.

1056
00:52:52,436 --> 00:52:54,177
Come again tomorrow.

1057
00:52:54,177 --> 00:52:56,680
I guess we'll get another bag.

1058
00:52:57,074 --> 00:52:58,275
The things they do...

1059
00:52:58,275 --> 00:52:59,376
[Worried About The Bakery]

1060
00:53:00,310 --> 00:53:02,699
Thank you. Take care.

1061
00:53:07,250 --> 00:53:08,885
Look at us seniors, having a field day.

1062
00:53:08,885 --> 00:53:13,232
We're all going crazy for this bakery.

1063
00:53:14,958 --> 00:53:18,495
[The Voices Of Our Regular Customers]

1064
00:53:18,495 --> 00:53:21,999
You seem to be dropping by daily.

1065
00:53:21,999 --> 00:53:24,768
I'm not in great shape,

1066
00:53:24,768 --> 00:53:26,770
so I can't cook even if I want to.

1067
00:53:26,770 --> 00:53:30,741
I need to have these stocked at home.

1068
00:53:30,741 --> 00:53:34,645
I feel bad asking people for favors.

1069
00:53:34,645 --> 00:53:36,380
They wrapped it up like this,

1070
00:53:36,380 --> 00:53:38,571
so I can store it as it is.

1071
00:53:49,626 --> 00:53:50,794
My goodness.

1072
00:53:53,030 --> 00:53:54,503
There we go.

1073
00:53:57,034 --> 00:53:59,302
I can buy it myself, for goodness' sake.

1074
00:53:59,302 --> 00:54:00,303
Why go out of your way?

1075
00:54:00,303 --> 00:54:03,206
[They Are Squabbling]
I'm just thankful for all you do for me.

1076
00:54:03,206 --> 00:54:05,809
[A Friendly Tug-Of-War]
You are unbelievable.

1077
00:54:05,809 --> 00:54:07,244
I keep telling you not to.

1078
00:54:07,244 --> 00:54:08,979
I feel bad getting meals
from an old woman.

1079
00:54:08,979 --> 00:54:10,707
Don't feel bad.

1080
00:54:11,081 --> 00:54:12,227
- Ma'am.
- Yes?

1081
00:54:12,227 --> 00:54:15,686
Didn't you buy this so you could eat it?

1082
00:54:15,686 --> 00:54:16,753
She's my nephew's wife,

1083
00:54:16,753 --> 00:54:19,556
and she always takes good care of me,
even when I'm not well.

1084
00:54:19,556 --> 00:54:21,625
So I bought an extra one for her.

1085
00:54:21,625 --> 00:54:23,226
- My goodness.
- Yes.

1086
00:54:23,226 --> 00:54:24,962
Will you stop by later?

1087
00:54:24,962 --> 00:54:25,996
No?

1088
00:54:25,996 --> 00:54:27,434
[At First, It Was So Unfamiliar]

1089
00:54:27,434 --> 00:54:30,867
[That They Were Hesitant To Enter]
Have a nice day.

1090
00:54:30,867 --> 00:54:32,502
- Hello.
- Hello.

1091
00:54:32,502 --> 00:54:33,904
[But Then One Day]
Hello.

1092
00:54:33,904 --> 00:54:36,540
[They Worked Up The Courage To Walk In]

1093
00:54:36,540 --> 00:54:38,709
Welcome. Please sit here.

1094
00:54:38,709 --> 00:54:40,377
This is a gift from us.

1095
00:54:40,377 --> 00:54:41,378
Take the money.

1096
00:54:41,378 --> 00:54:44,214
[Then Came Again To Buy More Bread]
No, it's really okay.

1097
00:54:44,214 --> 00:54:46,717
[And Even Dropped By For No Reason]
I put in two jam pods.

1098
00:54:46,717 --> 00:54:48,051
- See you tomorrow.
- All right.

1099
00:54:48,051 --> 00:54:49,619
- Get home safely.
- Bye.

1100
00:54:49,619 --> 00:54:52,489
Let's place them here.

1101
00:54:52,489 --> 00:54:53,590
[Their Hesitant Steps]

1102
00:54:53,590 --> 00:54:58,095
[Have Grown Much Lighter]

1103
00:55:00,764 --> 00:55:03,400
I understand how they feel.

1104
00:55:03,400 --> 00:55:05,235
- I know why they come every day.
- Exactly.

1105
00:55:05,235 --> 00:55:09,172
And also, they feel uplifted
whenever they come here.

1106
00:55:12,709 --> 00:55:14,211
Aren't they so sweet?

1107
00:55:14,211 --> 00:55:16,947
It's amazing their stomach can handle it.

1108
00:55:20,717 --> 00:55:23,453
- Welcome.
- Hello, come on in.

1109
00:55:23,453 --> 00:55:26,323
You look so young.
You must be over 65 years old to enter.

1110
00:55:26,323 --> 00:55:27,390
May I check your ID?

1111
00:55:27,390 --> 00:55:29,860
- Welcome.
- You just look too young.

1112
00:55:29,860 --> 00:55:31,528
[The Manager Approves]

1113
00:55:32,963 --> 00:55:34,698
- I'm a little doubtful.
- You're a bit doubtful?

1114
00:55:34,698 --> 00:55:35,699
Yes.

1115
00:55:37,634 --> 00:55:39,503
You passed the ID check.

1116
00:55:39,503 --> 00:55:40,570
- She passed?
- She passed?

1117
00:55:40,570 --> 00:55:42,009
Come this way.

1118
00:55:42,639 --> 00:55:44,841
- You came with your granddaughter, right?
- Yes.

1119
00:55:44,841 --> 00:55:48,145
- You have a great memory.
- The smart one.

1120
00:55:48,545 --> 00:55:51,548
My granddaughter just started third grade.

1121
00:55:51,548 --> 00:55:54,651
She was elected class president,
so we came to celebrate.

1122
00:55:54,651 --> 00:55:57,721
Congratulations. You look like a smart girl.

1123
00:55:57,721 --> 00:55:59,362
- She is...
- I'm her mother.

1124
00:55:59,362 --> 00:56:01,925
[She Came With Her Daughter Today]
I'm her mother.

1125
00:56:01,925 --> 00:56:04,494
- Must be nice.
- Are you ready to order?

1126
00:56:04,494 --> 00:56:05,829
- Yes.
- Okay.

1127
00:56:05,829 --> 00:56:07,564
- Vanilla latte...
- I'll have an iced vanilla latte.

1128
00:56:07,564 --> 00:56:10,467
- And one hot vanilla latte.
- One hot vanilla latte.

1129
00:56:11,034 --> 00:56:14,070
[He Gets Right On It
Before They Finish Ordering]

1130
00:56:39,162 --> 00:56:41,398
Here is one hot vanilla latte and...

1131
00:56:41,398 --> 00:56:43,433
The other half of the heart

1132
00:56:43,433 --> 00:56:46,069
- will be added next time.
- All right.

1133
00:56:46,770 --> 00:56:48,705
I'll complete it next time you come.

1134
00:56:48,705 --> 00:56:50,807
[A New Concept]
I can't give out two hearts so easily.

1135
00:56:50,807 --> 00:56:52,609
[Failure Heart Reward System]
I can't do that.

1136
00:56:53,543 --> 00:56:56,379
Take half a heart today,

1137
00:56:56,379 --> 00:56:57,747
and I'll fill it out next time.

1138
00:56:57,747 --> 00:56:59,449
Make sure to remind me.

1139
00:56:59,449 --> 00:57:01,418
- Can we take a picture of it?
- Of course.

1140
00:57:01,418 --> 00:57:03,653
I'm not embarrassed by my work.

1141
00:57:03,653 --> 00:57:05,306
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

1142
00:57:06,690 --> 00:57:08,792
He's very friendly.

1143
00:57:09,348 --> 00:57:10,961
He's so lovable,

1144
00:57:10,961 --> 00:57:13,363
even though he's someone else's son.

1145
00:57:13,363 --> 00:57:14,431
All right.

1146
00:57:14,431 --> 00:57:16,266
I wish my son would grow up like that.

1147
00:57:16,266 --> 00:57:17,734
Well, my son is all grown up,

1148
00:57:17,734 --> 00:57:20,904
but there's still hope for your son.

1149
00:57:25,475 --> 00:57:28,478
[With No Risk Of Falling]

1150
00:57:28,478 --> 00:57:32,449
[Only Four-Wheels Were Seen In The Village]

1151
00:57:34,351 --> 00:57:36,586
[But An Unusual Rider
Has Turned Up On Two Wheels]

1152
00:57:36,987 --> 00:57:38,855
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

1153
00:57:42,826 --> 00:57:44,594
- You can sit-
- I'm not over 65 years old.

1154
00:57:45,562 --> 00:57:49,232
[The Café's Only Downside]

1155
00:57:49,232 --> 00:57:50,600
[They Have To Turn Him Away]

1156
00:57:50,600 --> 00:57:53,136
In that case, unfortunately...

1157
00:57:53,136 --> 00:57:54,371
- It's the rule.
- You can't sell to other customers?

1158
00:57:54,371 --> 00:57:56,072
No, I'm sorry.

1159
00:57:56,072 --> 00:57:59,109
It's because my birth was registered late.

1160
00:58:01,618 --> 00:58:02,846
- It's a shame...
- Well,

1161
00:58:02,846 --> 00:58:04,714
- I...
- Yes?

1162
00:58:04,714 --> 00:58:07,584
I boasted so much about coming here

1163
00:58:07,584 --> 00:58:09,486
that I must buy some bread.

1164
00:58:09,486 --> 00:58:11,688
[I Made A Big Show Of It]

1165
00:58:12,155 --> 00:58:15,058
- Where are you from?
- I'm a local.

1166
00:58:15,058 --> 00:58:17,961
I can't sell it to you,
as word might get out.

1167
00:58:17,961 --> 00:58:22,098
I'm so sorry.
We really want to, but it's the rule.

1168
00:58:22,098 --> 00:58:24,200
[Conflicted]

1169
00:58:25,435 --> 00:58:26,336
[Watching Other Customers Enter Brazenly]

1170
00:58:26,336 --> 00:58:28,371
- It's not possible?
- I'm afraid not.

1171
00:58:28,371 --> 00:58:29,839
[It's A Bitter Pill To Swallow]

1172
00:58:34,377 --> 00:58:36,613
[It's A Shame]

1173
00:58:36,613 --> 00:58:40,617
[But He Walks Away For Now]

1174
00:58:40,617 --> 00:58:41,889
[Maybe Not?]

1175
00:58:41,889 --> 00:58:44,688
[Pops In]
If you look at the menu...

1176
00:58:44,688 --> 00:58:45,722
Welcome...

1177
00:58:45,722 --> 00:58:47,324
If I come back with someone over 65,

1178
00:58:47,324 --> 00:58:48,858
- can I buy something?
- Yes, if you do that,

1179
00:58:48,858 --> 00:58:49,893
- you can eat here.
- I can?

1180
00:58:49,893 --> 00:58:50,827
- Of course.
- Okay.

1181
00:58:50,827 --> 00:58:53,027
[He Double-Checks The Rules]
Come back with someone else.

1182
00:58:53,897 --> 00:58:57,767
[And Leaves In A Not-So-Cool Way]

1183
00:58:59,002 --> 00:59:00,904
[10 Minutes Later]

1184
00:59:00,904 --> 00:59:02,505
[Rolling Up]

1185
00:59:03,039 --> 00:59:07,243
[He's Back Again!]

1186
00:59:08,945 --> 00:59:12,182
[He's Joined By A Mystery Man]

1187
00:59:13,550 --> 00:59:15,285
[2nd Attempt To Enter]

1188
00:59:15,685 --> 00:59:18,021
He must have brought someone over 65.

1189
00:59:18,021 --> 00:59:19,689
You came with a senior.

1190
00:59:19,689 --> 00:59:21,358
- Is he older?
- He's my friend.

1191
00:59:21,358 --> 00:59:22,358
[Friend Steps In]

1192
00:59:22,807 --> 00:59:25,028
[Ko Gwang Mun The Lifesaver]

1193
00:59:25,028 --> 00:59:27,831
So you were telling the truth
about your birth record?

1194
00:59:27,831 --> 00:59:29,466
I told you so.

1195
00:59:29,466 --> 00:59:31,601
[Proving It With His White Hair]
You two are friends?

1196
00:59:31,601 --> 00:59:34,170
He dragged me here from work.

1197
00:59:34,170 --> 00:59:36,139
It's good of you to come.

1198
00:59:37,040 --> 00:59:39,409
[Ko Kwang I Registered As 64 Years Old]

1199
00:59:39,409 --> 00:59:43,980
I want to buy a set as a gift for someone.

1200
00:59:43,980 --> 00:59:46,383
Whatever you recommend is fine.

1201
00:59:46,383 --> 00:59:47,918
Just wrap it up nicely.

1202
00:59:47,918 --> 00:59:49,319
This here...

1203
00:59:49,319 --> 00:59:52,655
I also want to get a variety

1204
00:59:52,655 --> 00:59:54,791
[2 Sets Of Baked Goods]
so that a number of people can share it.

1205
00:59:54,791 --> 00:59:56,192
I told a lot of people about this place.

1206
00:59:56,192 --> 00:59:58,228
So I must be allowed in.

1207
00:59:58,228 --> 01:00:00,296
They asked me to buy bread.

1208
01:00:00,296 --> 01:00:01,431
[He's Still Upset]
In that case...

1209
01:00:01,431 --> 01:00:04,134
[I Hope You'll Feel Better]
In that case, I'll just mix and match.

1210
01:00:04,134 --> 01:00:05,368
[After A Lovely Dessert]
I'll put together two sets.

1211
01:00:05,368 --> 01:00:07,437
- I'll put together two sets.
- Please make one extra nice.

1212
01:00:07,437 --> 01:00:08,671
- One of them must be extra nice?
- Yes.

1213
01:00:08,671 --> 01:00:09,839
It must be very pretty.

1214
01:00:09,839 --> 01:00:11,141
That's tricky.

1215
01:00:11,141 --> 01:00:13,343
But honestly,
we always wrap them up nicely.

1216
01:00:13,343 --> 01:00:14,878
We never do a sloppy job.

1217
01:00:16,279 --> 01:00:19,216
[Come To Think Of It]
That young man...

1218
01:00:19,216 --> 01:00:21,117
Isn't he a celebrity?

1219
01:00:21,117 --> 01:00:22,285
[Indifferent ]
I don't know.

1220
01:00:22,285 --> 01:00:24,988
- He's famous.
- Is that right?

1221
01:00:25,388 --> 01:00:26,456
What did he star in?

1222
01:00:26,456 --> 01:00:28,324
- Who? Me?
- Yes.

1223
01:00:28,324 --> 01:00:30,393
[Where Did I See This Young Man?]
I was

1224
01:00:30,393 --> 01:00:32,262
in a drama called <i>Hometown Cha-Cha-Cha</i>.

1225
01:00:32,262 --> 01:00:34,264
[We Don't Know It]
It aired a while back.

1226
01:00:34,264 --> 01:00:36,433
You don't know it, do you?
I was also in <i>2 Days &amp; 1 Night</i>.

1227
01:00:36,433 --> 01:00:39,102
Aside from <i>2 Days &amp; 1 Night</i>,
there was something else.

1228
01:00:39,102 --> 01:00:40,670
<i>Can This Love Be Translated?</i>

1229
01:00:40,670 --> 01:00:42,138
I think it was a movie.

1230
01:00:42,138 --> 01:00:43,173
<i>The Childe?</i>

1231
01:00:43,173 --> 01:00:44,627
[Are You Listing Your Resume?]

1232
01:00:44,627 --> 01:00:45,675
[Awkward Giggle]

1233
01:00:45,675 --> 01:00:46,876
I've been in a variety of things.

1234
01:00:46,876 --> 01:00:48,511
[Ending With A Goofy Grin]

1235
01:00:48,511 --> 01:00:50,914
Sir, you're very stylish.

1236
01:00:50,914 --> 01:00:52,315
- Am I?
- Yes.

1237
01:00:52,315 --> 01:00:53,983
- Thank you.
- Your glasses are very stylish, too.

1238
01:00:53,983 --> 01:00:55,051
[Blushing]

1239
01:00:55,718 --> 01:00:57,454
- He's a professor.
- What?

1240
01:00:57,454 --> 01:00:58,555
He teaches at a university.

1241
01:00:58,555 --> 01:01:00,323
Oh, you're a professor?

1242
01:01:00,323 --> 01:01:01,658
[Our Customer With The Stylish Glasses]
That explains it.

1243
01:01:01,658 --> 01:01:03,460
[With A Fondness For Pretty Desserts]
Yes.

1244
01:01:03,893 --> 01:01:06,463
[Is The Brains Of Gapyeong Village]
Why didn't you tell them?

1245
01:01:06,463 --> 01:01:09,032
Who are you buying all this for?

1246
01:01:09,032 --> 01:01:10,733
[Saying It For A Third Time]
I boasted to a lot of people

1247
01:01:10,733 --> 01:01:13,419
at the center where I play tennis.

1248
01:01:14,871 --> 01:01:18,608
[We Will Fill These Boxes
To The Brim For You]

1249
01:01:18,608 --> 01:01:20,543
Did you go to the bakery?

1250
01:01:20,543 --> 01:01:23,480
- They said I couldn't enter at first.
- Why?

1251
01:01:23,480 --> 01:01:26,216
You're an old man as well.

1252
01:01:26,216 --> 01:01:28,751
[He's Venting On His Way Home]
He's a professor, after all.

1253
01:01:28,751 --> 01:01:31,488
- My birth was registered late.
- Really?

1254
01:01:31,488 --> 01:01:33,408
- I'm officially a year younger.
- Is that right?

1255
01:01:36,025 --> 01:01:37,327
[And Perhaps]

1256
01:01:37,327 --> 01:01:40,096
[Familiar Footsteps]

1257
01:01:41,131 --> 01:01:42,599
[Ko Gwang Hyeon]
Hello.

1258
01:01:42,599 --> 01:01:43,933
Welcome!

1259
01:01:43,933 --> 01:01:45,468
Welcome. Hello, sir!

1260
01:01:45,468 --> 01:01:48,538
You always sit here.

1261
01:01:49,606 --> 01:01:52,475
[He Sits In The Same Seat As Usual]

1262
01:01:52,475 --> 01:01:53,776
- One milk coffee.
- Milk coffee?

1263
01:01:53,776 --> 01:01:55,612
- I'll bring you a café latte.
- Okay.

1264
01:01:56,579 --> 01:01:58,214
It's been a while since I last saw you.

1265
01:01:58,214 --> 01:01:59,782
I know, right?

1266
01:02:01,718 --> 01:02:05,121
Were you so concerned
that business wasn't doing well?

1267
01:02:05,121 --> 01:02:07,190
Did you come to help us out?

1268
01:02:07,190 --> 01:02:09,826
I should come here more often as a local.

1269
01:02:09,826 --> 01:02:12,595
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1270
01:02:12,595 --> 01:02:15,632
Working is more fun when business is good.

1271
01:02:15,632 --> 01:02:18,935
- I'm in a good mood, thanks to you.
- That's good.

1272
01:02:19,669 --> 01:02:22,405
[Seon Ho Presents Our Regular Customer]

1273
01:02:24,774 --> 01:02:26,643
[With A Heart-Like Heart]

1274
01:02:27,210 --> 01:02:29,045
Since this is your third visit...

1275
01:02:32,282 --> 01:02:35,118
Third-time customers get this heart.

1276
01:02:35,118 --> 01:02:36,286
- A small heart is possible.
- A small heart?

1277
01:02:36,286 --> 01:02:37,320
Yes, a small heart.

1278
01:02:37,320 --> 01:02:39,455
It gets bigger if you come a fourth time.

1279
01:02:41,457 --> 01:02:43,193
[With His Usual Elegance]

1280
01:02:43,193 --> 01:02:46,462
[He Eats With His Knife And Fork]

1281
01:02:46,462 --> 01:02:48,398
[Wireless Earbuds]

1282
01:02:49,098 --> 01:02:50,833
[With His Wireless Earbuds In]

1283
01:02:50,833 --> 01:02:54,204
[He Vibes To His Own Personal Soundtrack]

1284
01:02:55,872 --> 01:02:57,340
[While He Fully Enjoys]

1285
01:02:57,340 --> 01:03:00,577
[The French Dessert]

1286
01:03:02,212 --> 01:03:04,714
[Cleaning Up The Crumbs]

1287
01:03:05,682 --> 01:03:07,650
[66-Year-Old Hipster Solo Bakery Enthusiast]

1288
01:03:07,650 --> 01:03:10,620
[In The Flesh]

1289
01:03:11,421 --> 01:03:15,225
[Another Group Of Hipster Seniors
Dressed In Pink]

1290
01:03:17,126 --> 01:03:18,828
It's not bad.

1291
01:03:19,729 --> 01:03:22,298
It's tasty.

1292
01:03:26,169 --> 01:03:27,169
[Glances Over]

1293
01:03:28,438 --> 01:03:29,438
[Another Glance]

1294
01:03:29,806 --> 01:03:30,806
[Glancing Again]

1295
01:03:31,608 --> 01:03:34,277
[Her Eyes Keep Straying Somewhere]

1296
01:03:34,811 --> 01:03:38,114
[Staring]

1297
01:03:38,548 --> 01:03:41,484
[Her Object Of Interest]

1298
01:03:41,484 --> 01:03:43,953
[Sensing Her Stare]

1299
01:03:43,953 --> 01:03:45,455
[Eye Contact]

1300
01:03:48,524 --> 01:03:49,759
Does it taste okay?

1301
01:03:49,759 --> 01:03:51,461
[Giggle]

1302
01:03:51,461 --> 01:03:53,630
What is it? Do I look funny?

1303
01:03:53,630 --> 01:03:55,798
[Just Looking At Him Makes Her Laugh]

1304
01:03:55,798 --> 01:03:57,500
Why are you smiling at me?

1305
01:03:57,500 --> 01:03:59,636
- You're a sweetheart.
- Yay.

1306
01:03:59,636 --> 01:04:01,087
Yay.

1307
01:04:01,638 --> 01:04:02,927
Nice.

1308
01:04:05,742 --> 01:04:07,677
Are you closing the bakery after today?

1309
01:04:07,677 --> 01:04:09,545
- No, we're open tomorrow.
- Will you be closed after tomorrow?

1310
01:04:09,545 --> 01:04:11,147
Will you come again tomorrow?

1311
01:04:11,147 --> 01:04:12,378
No.

1312
01:04:13,783 --> 01:04:16,636
I'm a country woman. What do I know?

1313
01:04:17,687 --> 01:04:18,788
What do you think?

1314
01:04:18,788 --> 01:04:20,256
Did we bring you some joy?

1315
01:04:20,256 --> 01:04:21,991
Yeah, it's nice.

1316
01:04:21,991 --> 01:04:24,101
We got to see famous celebrities.

1317
01:04:26,195 --> 01:04:27,630
- Welcome.
- Hello.

1318
01:04:27,630 --> 01:04:29,365
- Hello.
- Hello.

1319
01:04:29,365 --> 01:04:31,434
- Hello.
- How big is your party?

1320
01:04:31,434 --> 01:04:32,935
- There are four of us.
- Four?

1321
01:04:32,935 --> 01:04:35,772
- What are you doing here?
- Oh, my.

1322
01:04:35,772 --> 01:04:38,141
- Look who it is.
- How have you been?

1323
01:04:38,141 --> 01:04:40,877
I can't believe I'm running into you here.

1324
01:04:40,877 --> 01:04:43,513
What a surprise.

1325
01:04:43,913 --> 01:04:45,815
[A Gathering Spot For The Local Seniors]

1326
01:04:45,815 --> 01:04:47,784
[Buseong Village,
Gapyeong Village, Seodangchon Village]

1327
01:04:47,784 --> 01:04:49,252
- Have you eaten?
- Yes.

1328
01:04:49,252 --> 01:04:50,593
Are you leaving?

1329
01:04:50,593 --> 01:04:52,588
Goodbye.

1330
01:04:52,588 --> 01:04:54,324
Bye.

1331
01:04:55,058 --> 01:04:56,793
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

1332
01:04:58,494 --> 01:05:00,096
Where are you all from?

1333
01:05:00,096 --> 01:05:01,731
We all live in Gochang.

1334
01:05:01,731 --> 01:05:04,100
How come you're all so stylish?

1335
01:05:04,100 --> 01:05:06,569
We dressed up to come here.

1336
01:05:08,037 --> 01:05:09,439
I think I saw on TV...

1337
01:05:09,439 --> 01:05:11,574
- You think you've seen me on TV, right?
- Yes.

1338
01:05:11,574 --> 01:05:13,917
You're Seon Ho.

1339
01:05:14,344 --> 01:05:15,578
That's right.

1340
01:05:15,578 --> 01:05:16,713
- You're handsome.
- You're handsome.

1341
01:05:16,713 --> 01:05:17,814
- Really?
- You look better in person.

1342
01:05:17,814 --> 01:05:19,282
- Do I look better in person?
- Yeah.

1343
01:05:19,282 --> 01:05:21,217
I've heard I look better on TV.

1344
01:05:21,217 --> 01:05:23,786
But what do they know, right?

1345
01:05:23,786 --> 01:05:25,663
You're better looking in person.

1346
01:05:26,989 --> 01:05:28,191
[Their Order Is Served]
My goodness.

1347
01:05:28,191 --> 01:05:30,660
- Hello.
- Thank you.

1348
01:05:33,996 --> 01:05:37,033
This one... It tastes better if you stir it first.

1349
01:05:37,033 --> 01:05:38,234
- Okay.
- Okay.

1350
01:05:38,234 --> 01:05:40,737
- I like this one.
- All right.

1351
01:05:40,737 --> 01:05:42,672
Here, eat up.

1352
01:05:42,672 --> 01:05:44,774
I'm just going to use my hands.

1353
01:05:44,774 --> 01:05:46,843
- It's tasty.
- It's very good.

1354
01:05:46,843 --> 01:05:48,845
- It's nice and crunchy.
- It's delicious.

1355
01:05:48,845 --> 01:05:51,080
[Bonjour Green Barley Field Tart]
I don't think this is bread.

1356
01:05:51,080 --> 01:05:52,615
I guess not.

1357
01:05:52,615 --> 01:05:54,751
- I can't cut it no matter how hard I try.
- Try eating it.

1358
01:05:54,751 --> 01:05:57,186
You're meant to eat that base.

1359
01:05:57,186 --> 01:05:58,821
- No, you're not.
- You're not?

1360
01:05:58,821 --> 01:06:00,323
It's not edible.

1361
01:06:00,323 --> 01:06:02,024
I can't cut it.

1362
01:06:02,024 --> 01:06:02,992
[Tap]

1363
01:06:02,992 --> 01:06:04,160
This is a biscuit.

1364
01:06:04,160 --> 01:06:05,995
I'm telling you, it's edible.

1365
01:06:07,363 --> 01:06:08,998
- I guess it is a biscuit.
- It is.

1366
01:06:08,998 --> 01:06:11,532
- It's a biscuit.
- Yes, it is.

1367
01:06:13,569 --> 01:06:16,072
- That was good.
- Yes, it was.

1368
01:06:16,072 --> 01:06:17,240
[A Very Satisfying Dessert Time]

1369
01:06:17,240 --> 01:06:18,141
[Sweep]

1370
01:06:18,141 --> 01:06:20,510
- She's so pretty with her tiny face.
- Right?

1371
01:06:20,510 --> 01:06:21,844
[Sweep]

1372
01:06:22,311 --> 01:06:26,349
[Wiping The Table Clean]

1373
01:06:26,349 --> 01:06:27,250
No need to clean up.

1374
01:06:27,250 --> 01:06:28,851
- I'll do that.
- Okay.

1375
01:06:28,851 --> 01:06:30,986
That's my job. Leave it alone.

1376
01:06:32,021 --> 01:06:34,257
You don't need to do that. I want to do it.

1377
01:06:34,257 --> 01:06:35,258
[In That Case, We'll Take Our Leave]

1378
01:06:35,258 --> 01:06:37,360
- Seon Ho is doing the heavy work.
- Thank you for the food.

1379
01:06:37,360 --> 01:06:39,529
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1380
01:06:39,529 --> 01:06:41,831
- We enjoyed it.
- Please come again.

1381
01:06:41,831 --> 01:06:44,373
- Come again. Thank you.
- Thank you.

1382
01:06:45,902 --> 01:06:48,905
[More Customers Leave]

1383
01:06:50,907 --> 01:06:52,675
[Sighs]

1384
01:06:53,376 --> 01:06:58,514
[It's Afternoon Slump Time]

1385
01:06:59,649 --> 01:07:01,884
[This Won't Do!]

1386
01:07:06,389 --> 01:07:10,426
[Cutting It Into Bite-Sized Pieces]

1387
01:07:11,594 --> 01:07:14,197
It's time for a pick-me-up.

1388
01:07:15,998 --> 01:07:17,524
It's time for a pick-me-up.

1389
01:07:20,102 --> 01:07:21,404
Eat up.

1390
01:07:21,404 --> 01:07:23,272
[A Treat For The Staff]
Thank you.

1391
01:07:23,272 --> 01:07:24,407
[Courtesy Of The Manager]
Come quickly.

1392
01:07:24,407 --> 01:07:26,108
Honestly,

1393
01:07:26,108 --> 01:07:27,577
I lost us a fair bit of money today

1394
01:07:27,577 --> 01:07:29,145
- by giving out a lot of freebies.
- Well done.

1395
01:07:29,145 --> 01:07:32,281
I'll enjoy this even if I'm at fault.

1396
01:07:32,281 --> 01:07:33,612
Good work today.

1397
01:07:35,221 --> 01:07:36,786
- Is it good?
- Yes, it's so good.

1398
01:07:37,610 --> 01:07:38,888
- It's so refreshing.
- Is it good?

1399
01:07:38,888 --> 01:07:40,389
Yes, it's so good.

1400
01:07:42,492 --> 01:07:44,012
I'm so curious about the <i>bokbunja</i> one.

1401
01:07:49,031 --> 01:07:50,266
[Hesitant]

1402
01:07:50,266 --> 01:07:52,969
- I'll have just one more bite.
- Eat up. You're a big guy.

1403
01:07:52,969 --> 01:07:54,904
Have some more, Joo Bin.

1404
01:07:54,904 --> 01:07:56,906
Doesn't it give you an energy boost?

1405
01:07:56,906 --> 01:07:58,574
[While The Hall Team Recharge]

1406
01:07:58,574 --> 01:07:59,942
"Otoki Light and Easy..."

1407
01:07:59,942 --> 01:08:02,044
[Kitchen Team Also Recharge]
Otoki released a "Light and Easy" line.

1408
01:08:02,044 --> 01:08:04,413
Chicken breast corn dog?

1409
01:08:04,413 --> 01:08:06,916
[Opens It Immediately]

1410
01:08:08,317 --> 01:08:10,520
This is a great quick meal.

1411
01:08:13,389 --> 01:08:15,925
This is so convenient.

1412
01:08:15,925 --> 01:08:16,859
- What do you think?
- Yes.

1413
01:08:16,859 --> 01:08:18,661
If you don't have time for breakfast,

1414
01:08:18,661 --> 01:08:20,963
this is a convenient substitute.

1415
01:08:20,963 --> 01:08:22,932
[A Soft, Springy Corn Dog
That's Perfect For Breakfast On The Go]

1416
01:08:22,932 --> 01:08:26,435
[Bonjour Bakery]

1417
01:08:34,043 --> 01:08:36,779
- It feels like someone's coming.
- She has a Bonjour bag.

1418
01:08:36,779 --> 01:08:40,249
All the locals have that canvas bag.

1419
01:08:40,249 --> 01:08:41,317
[Returning Customer?]

1420
01:08:41,317 --> 01:08:43,119
- Is she coming in?
- Is she?

1421
01:08:43,519 --> 01:08:45,688
She's the one who forgot her wallet

1422
01:08:45,688 --> 01:08:47,857
- and came back to pay her tab yesterday.
- Really?

1423
01:08:47,857 --> 01:08:49,443
Here she comes.

1424
01:08:55,998 --> 01:08:58,334
Come on in.

1425
01:08:58,334 --> 01:09:00,202
- Did you come alone?
- She came with her husband.

1426
01:09:00,202 --> 01:09:01,804
You came with your husband.

1427
01:09:01,804 --> 01:09:02,972
- Take a seat over there.
- Welcome.

1428
01:09:02,972 --> 01:09:04,707
- Sit further in since it's cold.
- Hello.

1429
01:09:04,707 --> 01:09:06,809
[Welcome To The Village Of Living Tradition]

1430
01:09:07,243 --> 01:09:08,277
Welcome.

1431
01:09:08,277 --> 01:09:10,279
- You came back.
- Welcome.

1432
01:09:10,880 --> 01:09:12,081
Welcome.

1433
01:09:12,081 --> 01:09:14,250
What does "Bonjour" mean?

1434
01:09:14,250 --> 01:09:16,218
- Is it a person's name?
- No.

1435
01:09:16,218 --> 01:09:17,620
It's a type of greeting.

1436
01:09:17,620 --> 01:09:19,055
"Bonjour."

1437
01:09:19,055 --> 01:09:21,090
Bonjour Bakery.

1438
01:09:21,090 --> 01:09:22,692
Welcome.

1439
01:09:22,692 --> 01:09:25,002
Over here. Sit there.

1440
01:09:26,362 --> 01:09:27,897
Jeez.

1441
01:09:30,333 --> 01:09:32,568
[Seems Like She Dragged Him]
It seems she came with her husband today.

1442
01:09:32,568 --> 01:09:34,036
[Against His Will]
She came alone yesterday.

1443
01:09:34,036 --> 01:09:35,471
[Grumble]

1444
01:09:36,372 --> 01:09:39,542
[Reluctantly Makes It To The Chair]
It's nice.

1445
01:09:41,110 --> 01:09:43,245
Would you like some bread?

1446
01:09:43,245 --> 01:09:45,047
- No, I just need some coffee.
- Coffee?

1447
01:09:45,781 --> 01:09:47,817
- We have bread at home.
- You do?

1448
01:09:47,817 --> 01:09:50,686
Why don't I make you a vanilla latte?

1449
01:09:50,686 --> 01:09:52,588
It's a sweet coffee with milk.

1450
01:09:52,588 --> 01:09:53,856
It's like instant sweet coffee.

1451
01:09:53,856 --> 01:09:55,625
- Is that okay?
- Anything with milk is fine.

1452
01:09:55,625 --> 01:09:57,593
Anything with milk.

1453
01:09:57,593 --> 01:10:00,863
Didn't you come alone yesterday?

1454
01:10:00,863 --> 01:10:03,566
- I see you brought your husband today.
- That's right.

1455
01:10:03,566 --> 01:10:04,600
I made him come.

1456
01:10:04,600 --> 01:10:05,601
- She felt bad.
- Sorry?

1457
01:10:05,601 --> 01:10:08,504
- I felt bad.
- She felt guilty.

1458
01:10:08,504 --> 01:10:10,106
That's elderly women for you.

1459
01:10:10,106 --> 01:10:12,575
[They Want To Share The Nice Things]

1460
01:10:13,042 --> 01:10:15,077
- The bread is delicious.
- It is.

1461
01:10:15,077 --> 01:10:17,613
I think this is on the house,
courtesy of Manager Hee Ae.

1462
01:10:17,613 --> 01:10:18,948
[1 Bonjour Financier On The House]
My goodness.

1463
01:10:18,948 --> 01:10:20,650
- The financier...
- That coffee looks great.

1464
01:10:20,650 --> 01:10:22,518
- It looks tasty, doesn't it?
- Yes.

1465
01:10:22,952 --> 01:10:25,105
I made it.

1466
01:10:25,688 --> 01:10:28,257
Cut the bread and enjoy.

1467
01:10:35,131 --> 01:10:36,866
It's good.

1468
01:10:48,511 --> 01:10:50,646
Try this. It's tasty.

1469
01:10:51,681 --> 01:10:55,618
[I Prefer Coffee Over Bread]

1470
01:10:57,720 --> 01:11:00,122
Is it really okay for us
to leave after eating this?

1471
01:11:00,523 --> 01:11:02,992
[She Feels Uneasy About The Free Financier]
Can you leave after eating it?

1472
01:11:02,992 --> 01:11:05,995
It was so good I feel bad not paying.

1473
01:11:05,995 --> 01:11:07,870
It's no problem at all.

1474
01:11:08,397 --> 01:11:12,766
This lady looks just like Kim Hee Ae.

1475
01:11:12,766 --> 01:11:13,736
She does, right?

1476
01:11:13,736 --> 01:11:15,638
[Adding To Her Confusion ]
She hears that a lot.

1477
01:11:15,638 --> 01:11:17,039
[Awkward Laugh]

1478
01:11:17,707 --> 01:11:19,975
- She is Kim Hee Ae.
- I...

1479
01:11:19,975 --> 01:11:21,944
- I said yesterday...
- It's her.

1480
01:11:21,944 --> 01:11:23,479
[She Thinks It's A Joke]
It's because I saw her drama recently.

1481
01:11:23,479 --> 01:11:26,615
Yes, this is her.

1482
01:11:26,615 --> 01:11:30,319
- Are you being serious?
- Yes, it's her.

1483
01:11:30,319 --> 01:11:32,088
- Did you not know?
- I had no idea.

1484
01:11:32,088 --> 01:11:34,490
It's written on her name tag.

1485
01:11:34,490 --> 01:11:38,427
I thought she had the same face!

1486
01:11:39,061 --> 01:11:40,963
You even came by yesterday.

1487
01:11:41,864 --> 01:11:43,733
[I Didn't Bring My Wallet]
Really?

1488
01:11:44,200 --> 01:11:47,670
[She Was Too Busy Opening A Tab]
I'll bring it later.

1489
01:11:47,670 --> 01:11:50,940
[She Never Imagined]
I'll come back.

1490
01:11:50,940 --> 01:11:53,175
[The Lady Before Her Was Kim Hee Ae]
I'm sorry.

1491
01:11:53,175 --> 01:11:55,711
[It's Me, Kim Hee Ae]

1492
01:11:57,947 --> 01:12:00,483
- It's nice to meet you.
- You even came by yesterday.

1493
01:12:00,483 --> 01:12:01,584
It's a pleasure.

1494
01:12:01,584 --> 01:12:02,985
Thank you.

1495
01:12:02,985 --> 01:12:06,889
- I don't think she knew.
- I really love watching your dramas.

1496
01:12:06,889 --> 01:12:07,923
I'm thrilled to meet you.

1497
01:12:07,923 --> 01:12:09,625
Thank you.

1498
01:12:13,162 --> 01:12:14,764
Here we go.

1499
01:12:15,397 --> 01:12:16,866
One, two...

1500
01:12:16,866 --> 01:12:17,933
Oh, we're doing this.

1501
01:12:18,834 --> 01:12:20,936
- That's so cute!
- This is...

1502
01:12:20,936 --> 01:12:23,372
One, two, three.

1503
01:12:23,372 --> 01:12:25,197
Ma'am, you're so cute.

1504
01:12:25,197 --> 01:12:27,243
[Giggle]
One, two, three.

1505
01:12:27,843 --> 01:12:29,678
You look so beautiful.

1506
01:12:30,980 --> 01:12:32,448
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1507
01:12:32,448 --> 01:12:33,516
Thank you.

1508
01:12:33,516 --> 01:12:35,451
- It's a real pleasure.
- Sure.

1509
01:12:37,720 --> 01:12:39,321
- Go home safely.
- It was nice meeting you.

1510
01:12:39,321 --> 01:12:40,623
Goodbye.

1511
01:12:40,623 --> 01:12:42,525
- It's so nice to meet you.
- Yes.

1512
01:12:42,525 --> 01:12:44,927
These azaleas are very pretty.

1513
01:12:44,927 --> 01:12:47,496
- The mountain is covered in azaleas.
- Azaleas?

1514
01:12:47,496 --> 01:12:49,532
- If you go up there...
- I see.

1515
01:12:49,532 --> 01:12:52,234
They're beautiful around a gravesite.

1516
01:12:52,234 --> 01:12:55,104
- Yes, they're very pretty and delicate.
- Right?

1517
01:12:57,606 --> 01:13:00,290
- Thank you. Take care.
- Goodbye.

1518
01:13:18,527 --> 01:13:21,764
[An Evening Feast To Thank Our Part-Timer, Joo Bin]

1519
01:13:32,408 --> 01:13:36,045
[Enjoying A Well-Deserved Meal]

1520
01:13:36,579 --> 01:13:39,448
[Great Work Today]

1521
01:13:39,448 --> 01:13:41,584
- Now that she's leaving...
- Why?

1522
01:13:41,584 --> 01:13:44,420
- There'll be so much more work.
- What are we going to do tomorrow?

1523
01:13:44,420 --> 01:13:46,555
- She's such a good worker.
- She works really well.

1524
01:13:46,555 --> 01:13:49,825
I didn't grow up with my grandparents,

1525
01:13:49,825 --> 01:13:51,327
so I find it hard to talk to older people.

1526
01:13:51,327 --> 01:13:54,330
I copied Seon Ho's words a lot.

1527
01:13:54,330 --> 01:13:57,032
He's so good at talking to people.

1528
01:13:57,032 --> 01:14:00,669
- That's because I'm used to the job now.
- Really?

1529
01:14:00,669 --> 01:14:03,205
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you for the food.

1530
01:14:03,205 --> 01:14:05,875
[Thank You For Your Hard Work,
Joo Bin, Our Dependable Part-Timer]

1531
01:14:07,743 --> 01:14:09,345
[It's Already The Night Before The Final Day]

1532
01:14:09,345 --> 01:14:10,512
Great work today.

1533
01:14:13,616 --> 01:14:15,551
Since tomorrow's the last day...

1534
01:14:15,551 --> 01:14:17,786
What else are you making tomorrow
besides the Cha Loaf Bread?

1535
01:14:17,786 --> 01:14:19,855
It's the one with forsythia.

1536
01:14:19,855 --> 01:14:22,091
- The one with forsythia.
- The Kumquat Forsythia Tart.

1537
01:14:22,091 --> 01:14:25,007
[That Won't Be Easy]

1538
01:14:25,007 --> 01:14:26,595
I'll have to try it,

1539
01:14:26,595 --> 01:14:29,064
but Saint-Honoré is the hardest.

1540
01:14:29,064 --> 01:14:31,506
But you did an incredible job.

1541
01:14:32,134 --> 01:14:34,870
By the end, he even added his own spin.

1542
01:14:34,870 --> 01:14:36,505
- Seung Won?
- Yeah.

1543
01:14:36,505 --> 01:14:39,141
Some people are just born
with that kind of natural instinct.

1544
01:14:39,141 --> 01:14:40,623
They have an adaptable mind.

1545
01:14:46,949 --> 01:14:49,885
[Manager Hee Ae Steps Out For A Brief Moment]

1546
01:14:49,885 --> 01:14:52,855
[To Breathe In The Fresh Air]
It's nice and cool out.

1547
01:14:58,994 --> 01:15:01,597
[She Enjoys The Fragrance Of Flowers
Carried In The Breeze]

1548
01:15:02,998 --> 01:15:04,800
[She Strolls Down The Path
Across From The Bakery]

1549
01:15:04,800 --> 01:15:08,003
[Which She Was Too Busy To Do]

1550
01:15:10,177 --> 01:15:11,525
Oh, my.

1551
01:15:13,676 --> 01:15:16,001
There's the spotted dog.

1552
01:15:17,313 --> 01:15:22,718
[Day One]
Yesterday, a car passed by,

1553
01:15:22,718 --> 01:15:26,021
and a dog was running after it.

1554
01:15:26,021 --> 01:15:28,958
It was a black-and-white dog.

1555
01:15:28,958 --> 01:15:31,226
I think it's a local dog.

1556
01:15:31,226 --> 01:15:33,162
[The Dog She's Had On Her Mind
Since Day One]

1557
01:15:34,663 --> 01:15:36,865
Goodness.

1558
01:15:36,865 --> 01:15:40,736
[She Finally Met Him
In The Yard Across From The Bakery]

1559
01:15:42,237 --> 01:15:43,973
Are you scared?

1560
01:15:48,110 --> 01:15:50,245
Are you hiding?

1561
01:15:50,245 --> 01:15:51,513
You poor thing.

1562
01:15:51,513 --> 01:15:52,982
[For The Sake Of The Scared Little Puppy]

1563
01:15:52,982 --> 01:15:54,350
All right.

1564
01:15:55,351 --> 01:15:57,286
I'll crouch down. You poor thing.

1565
01:15:57,286 --> 01:15:58,620
[She Lowers Herself To His Level]

1566
01:15:58,620 --> 01:16:01,290
Poor thing. I'm sorry I scared you.

1567
01:16:03,325 --> 01:16:05,761
All right.

1568
01:16:05,761 --> 01:16:07,907
I'm sorry.
